133enum class BacktrackingAction {
134 NoBacktracking,
135 JumpToDescendantEntryPoint,
136 JumpToIndirectAdjacentEntryPoint,
137 JumpToDescendantTreeWalkerEntryPoint,
138 JumpToIndirectAdjacentTreeWalkerEntryPoint,
139 JumpToDescendantTail,
140 JumpToDirectAdjacentTail
141};
142
143struct BacktrackingFlag {
144 enum {
145 DescendantEntryPoint = 1,
146 IndirectAdjacentEntryPoint = 1 << 1,
147 SaveDescendantBacktrackingStart = 1 << 2,
148 SaveAdjacentBacktrackingStart = 1 << 3,
149 DirectAdjacentTail = 1 << 4,
150 DescendantTail = 1 << 5,
151 InChainWithDescendantTail = 1 << 6,
152 InChainWithAdjacentTail = 1 << 7
153 };
154};

182enum class AttributeCaseSensitivity {
183 CaseSensitive,
184 // Some values are matched case-insensitively for HTML elements.
185 // That is a legacy behavior decided by HTMLDocument::isCaseSensitiveAttribute().
186 HTMLLegacyCaseInsensitive,
187 CaseInsensitive
188};
189
190static AttributeCaseSensitivity attributeSelectorCaseSensitivity(const CSSSelector& selector)
191{
192 ASSERT(selector.isAttributeSelector());
193
194 // This is by convention, the case is irrelevant for Set.
195 if (selector.match() == CSSSelector::Set)
196 return AttributeCaseSensitivity::CaseSensitive;
197
198 if (selector.attributeValueMatchingIsCaseInsensitive())
199 return AttributeCaseSensitivity::CaseInsensitive;
200 if (HTMLDocument::isCaseSensitiveAttribute(selector.attribute()))
201 return AttributeCaseSensitivity::CaseSensitive;
202 return AttributeCaseSensitivity::HTMLLegacyCaseInsensitive;
203}
204
205class AttributeMatchingInfo {
206public:
207 explicit AttributeMatchingInfo(const CSSSelector& selector)
208 : m_selector(&selector)
209 , m_attributeCaseSensitivity(attributeSelectorCaseSensitivity(selector))
210 {
211 ASSERT(!(m_attributeCaseSensitivity == AttributeCaseSensitivity::CaseInsensitive && !selector.attributeValueMatchingIsCaseInsensitive()));
212 ASSERT(!(selector.match() == CSSSelector::Set && m_attributeCaseSensitivity != AttributeCaseSensitivity::CaseSensitive));
213 }
214
215 AttributeCaseSensitivity attributeCaseSensitivity() const { return m_attributeCaseSensitivity; }
216 const CSSSelector& selector() const { return *m_selector; }
217
218private:
219 const CSSSelector* m_selector;
220 AttributeCaseSensitivity m_attributeCaseSensitivity;
221};

242struct SelectorFragment {
243 FragmentRelation relationToLeftFragment;
244 FragmentRelation relationToRightFragment;
245 FragmentPositionInRootFragments positionInRootFragments;
246 bool isRightmostOrAdjacent { false };
247
248 BacktrackingAction traversalBacktrackingAction = BacktrackingAction::NoBacktracking;
249 BacktrackingAction matchingTagNameBacktrackingAction = BacktrackingAction::NoBacktracking;
250 BacktrackingAction matchingPostTagNameBacktrackingAction = BacktrackingAction::NoBacktracking;
251 unsigned char backtrackingFlags = 0;
252 unsigned tagNameMatchedBacktrackingStartHeightFromDescendant = invalidHeight;
253 unsigned tagNameNotMatchedBacktrackingStartHeightFromDescendant = invalidHeight;
254 unsigned heightFromDescendant = 0;
255 unsigned tagNameMatchedBacktrackingStartWidthFromIndirectAdjacent = invalidWidth;
256 unsigned tagNameNotMatchedBacktrackingStartWidthFromIndirectAdjacent = invalidWidth;
257 unsigned widthFromIndirectAdjacent = 0;
258
259 // FIXME: the large stack allocation caused by the inline capacity causes memory inefficiency. We should dump
260 // the min/max/average of the vectors and pick better inline capacity.
261 const CSSSelector* tagNameSelector = nullptr;
262 const AtomString* id = nullptr;
263 Vector<const Vector<AtomString>*> languageArgumentsList;
264 Vector<const AtomStringImpl*, 8> classNames;
265 HashSet<unsigned> pseudoClasses;
266 Vector<JSC::FunctionPtr<JSC::OperationPtrTag>, 4> unoptimizedPseudoClasses;
267 Vector<AttributeMatchingInfo, 4> attributes;
268 Vector<std::pair<int, int>, 2> nthChildFilters;
269 Vector<NthChildOfSelectorInfo> nthChildOfFilters;
270 Vector<std::pair<int, int>, 2> nthLastChildFilters;
271 Vector<NthChildOfSelectorInfo> nthLastChildOfFilters;
272 SelectorList notFilters;
273 Vector<SelectorList> matchesFilters;
274 Vector<Vector<SelectorFragment>> anyFilters;
275 const CSSSelector* pseudoElementSelector = nullptr;
276
277 // For quirks mode, follow this: http://quirks.spec.whatwg.org/#the-:active-and-:hover-quirk
278 // In quirks mode, a compound selector 'selector' that matches the following conditions must not match elements that would not also match the ':any-link' selector.
279 //
280 // selector uses the ':active' or ':hover' pseudo-classes.
281 // selector does not use a type selector.
282 // selector does not use an attribute selector.
283 // selector does not use an ID selector.
284 // selector does not use a class selector.
285 // selector does not use a pseudo-class selector other than ':active' and ':hover'.
286 // selector does not use a pseudo-element selector.
287 // selector is not part of an argument to a functional pseudo-class or pseudo-element.
288 bool onlyMatchesLinksInQuirksMode = true;
289};

296 bool clobberElementAddressRegister = true;
297};

447const Assembler::RegisterID SelectorCodeGenerator::callFrameRegister = JSC::GPRInfo::callFrameRegister;
448
449enum class FragmentsLevel {
450 Root = 0,
451 InFunctionalPseudoType = 1
452};
453
454enum class PseudoElementMatchingBehavior { CanMatch, NeverMatch };
455
456static FunctionType constructFragments(const CSSSelector* rootSelector, SelectorContext, SelectorFragmentList& selectorFragments, FragmentsLevel, FragmentPositionInRootFragments, bool visitedMatchEnabled, VisitedMode&, PseudoElementMatchingBehavior);
457
458static void computeBacktrackingInformation(SelectorFragmentList& selectorFragments, unsigned level = 0);
459
460void compileSelector(CompiledSelector& compiledSelector, const CSSSelector* selector, SelectorContext selectorContext)
461{
462 ASSERT(compiledSelector.status == SelectorCompilationStatus::NotCompiled);
463
464 if (!JSC::Options::useJIT()) {
465 compiledSelector.status = SelectorCompilationStatus::CannotCompile;
466 return;
467 }
468
469 SelectorCodeGenerator codeGenerator(selector, selectorContext);
470 compiledSelector.status = codeGenerator.compile(compiledSelector.codeRef);
471
472#if defined(CSS_SELECTOR_JIT_PROFILING) && CSS_SELECTOR_JIT_PROFILING
473 compiledSelector.selector = selector;
474#endif
475
476 ASSERT(compiledSelector.status != SelectorCompilationStatus::NotCompiled);
477}
478
479static inline FragmentRelation fragmentRelationForSelectorRelation(CSSSelector::RelationType relation)
480{
481 switch (relation) {
482 case CSSSelector::DescendantSpace:
483 return FragmentRelation::Descendant;
484 case CSSSelector::Child:
485 return FragmentRelation::Child;
486 case CSSSelector::DirectAdjacent:
487 return FragmentRelation::DirectAdjacent;
488 case CSSSelector::IndirectAdjacent:
489 return FragmentRelation::IndirectAdjacent;
490 case CSSSelector::Subselector:
491 case CSSSelector::ShadowDescendant:
492 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
493 }
494 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
495 return FragmentRelation::Descendant;
496}
497
498static inline FunctionType mostRestrictiveFunctionType(FunctionType a, FunctionType b)
499{
500 return std::max(a, b);
501}
502
503static inline bool fragmentMatchesTheRightmostElement(const SelectorFragment& fragment)
504{
505 return fragment.relationToRightFragment == FragmentRelation::Rightmost && fragment.positionInRootFragments == FragmentPositionInRootFragments::Rightmost;
506}
507
508static inline bool fragmentMatchesRightmostOrAdjacentElement(const SelectorFragment& fragment)
509{
510 return fragment.isRightmostOrAdjacent && fragment.positionInRootFragments != FragmentPositionInRootFragments::Other;
511}
512
513static inline FunctionType addScrollbarPseudoClassType(const CSSSelector&, SelectorFragment&)
514{
515 // FIXME: scrollbar pseudoclass interaction with :not doesn't behave correctly.
516 // Compile them when they are fixed and tested.
517 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=146221
518 return FunctionType::CannotCompile;
519}
520
521// Handle the forward :nth-child() and backward :nth-last-child().
522static FunctionType addNthChildType(const CSSSelector& selector, SelectorContext selectorContext, FragmentPositionInRootFragments positionInRootFragments, CSSSelector::PseudoClassType firstMatchAlternative, bool visitedMatchEnabled, Vector<std::pair<int, int>, 2>& simpleCases, Vector<NthChildOfSelectorInfo>& filteredCases, HashSet<unsigned>& pseudoClasses)
523{
524 int a = selector.nthA();
525 int b = selector.nthB();
526
527 // The element count is always positive.
528 if (a <= 0 && b < 1)
529 return FunctionType::CannotMatchAnything;
530
531 if (const CSSSelectorList* selectorList = selector.selectorList()) {
532 NthChildOfSelectorInfo nthChildOfSelectorInfo;
533 nthChildOfSelectorInfo.a = a;
534 nthChildOfSelectorInfo.b = b;
535
536 FunctionType globalFunctionType = FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
537 if (selectorContext != SelectorContext::QuerySelector)
538 globalFunctionType = FunctionType::SelectorCheckerWithCheckingContext;
539
540 SelectorFragmentList* selectorFragments = nullptr;
541 for (const CSSSelector* subselector = selectorList->first(); subselector; subselector = CSSSelectorList::next(subselector)) {
542 if (!selectorFragments) {
543 nthChildOfSelectorInfo.selectorList.append(SelectorFragmentList());
544 selectorFragments = &nthChildOfSelectorInfo.selectorList.last();
545 }
546
547 VisitedMode ignoreVisitedMode = VisitedMode::None;
548 FunctionType functionType = constructFragments(subselector, selectorContext, *selectorFragments, FragmentsLevel::InFunctionalPseudoType, positionInRootFragments, visitedMatchEnabled, ignoreVisitedMode, PseudoElementMatchingBehavior::NeverMatch);
549 ASSERT_WITH_MESSAGE(ignoreVisitedMode == VisitedMode::None, ":visited is disabled in the functional pseudo classes");
550 switch (functionType) {
551 case FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker:
552 case FunctionType::SelectorCheckerWithCheckingContext:
553 break;
554 case FunctionType::CannotMatchAnything:
555 continue;
556 case FunctionType::CannotCompile:
557 return FunctionType::CannotCompile;
558 }
559
560 globalFunctionType = mostRestrictiveFunctionType(globalFunctionType, functionType);
561 selectorFragments = nullptr;
562 }
563
564 // If there is still a SelectorFragmentList open, the last Fragment(s) cannot match anything,
565 // we have one FragmentList too many in our selector list.
566 if (selectorFragments)
567 nthChildOfSelectorInfo.selectorList.removeLast();
568
569 if (nthChildOfSelectorInfo.selectorList.isEmpty())
570 return FunctionType::CannotMatchAnything;
571
572 filteredCases.append(nthChildOfSelectorInfo);
573 return globalFunctionType;
574 }
575
576 if (b == 1 && a <= 0)
577 pseudoClasses.add(firstMatchAlternative);
578 else
579 simpleCases.append(std::pair<int, int>(a, b));
580 if (selectorContext == SelectorContext::QuerySelector)
581 return FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
582 return FunctionType::SelectorCheckerWithCheckingContext;
583}
