763static inline FunctionType addPseudoClassType(const CSSSelector& selector, SelectorFragment& fragment, SelectorContext selectorContext, FragmentsLevel fragmentLevel, FragmentPositionInRootFragments positionInRootFragments, bool visitedMatchEnabled, VisitedMode& visitedMode, PseudoElementMatchingBehavior pseudoElementMatchingBehavior)
764{
765 CSSSelector::PseudoClassType type = selector.pseudoClassType();
766 switch (type) {
767 // Unoptimized pseudo selector. They are just function call to a simple testing function.
768 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassAutofill:
769 fragment.unoptimizedPseudoClasses.append(JSC::FunctionPtr<JSC::OperationPtrTag>(operationIsAutofilled));
770 return FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
771 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassAutofillStrongPassword:
772 fragment.unoptimizedPseudoClasses.append(JSC::FunctionPtr<JSC::OperationPtrTag>(operationIsAutofilledStrongPassword));
773 return FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
774 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassAutofillStrongPasswordViewable:
775 fragment.unoptimizedPseudoClasses.append(JSC::FunctionPtr<JSC::OperationPtrTag>(operationIsAutofilledStrongPasswordViewable));
776 return FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
777 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassChecked:
778 fragment.unoptimizedPseudoClasses.append(JSC::FunctionPtr<JSC::OperationPtrTag>(operationIsChecked));
779 return FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
780 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassDefault:
781 fragment.unoptimizedPseudoClasses.append(JSC::FunctionPtr<JSC::OperationPtrTag>(operationMatchesDefaultPseudoClass));
782 return FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
783 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassDisabled:
784 fragment.unoptimizedPseudoClasses.append(JSC::FunctionPtr<JSC::OperationPtrTag>(operationMatchesDisabledPseudoClass));
785 return FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
786 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassEnabled:
787 fragment.unoptimizedPseudoClasses.append(JSC::FunctionPtr<JSC::OperationPtrTag>(operationMatchesEnabledPseudoClass));
788 return FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
789 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassDefined:
790 fragment.unoptimizedPseudoClasses.append(JSC::FunctionPtr<JSC::OperationPtrTag>(operationIsDefinedElement));
791 return FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
792 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassDirectFocus:
793 fragment.unoptimizedPseudoClasses.append(JSC::FunctionPtr<JSC::OperationPtrTag>(operationMatchesDirectFocusPseudoClass));
794 return FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
795 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassFocus:
796 fragment.unoptimizedPseudoClasses.append(JSC::FunctionPtr<JSC::OperationPtrTag>(operationMatchesFocusPseudoClass));
797 return FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
798 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassFocusVisible:
799 fragment.unoptimizedPseudoClasses.append(JSC::FunctionPtr<JSC::OperationPtrTag>(operationMatchesFocusVisiblePseudoClass));
800 return FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
801 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassFocusWithin:
802 fragment.unoptimizedPseudoClasses.append(JSC::FunctionPtr<JSC::OperationPtrTag>(operationMatchesFocusWithinPseudoClass));
803 return FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
804 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassFullPageMedia:
805 fragment.unoptimizedPseudoClasses.append(JSC::FunctionPtr<JSC::OperationPtrTag>(operationIsMediaDocument));
806 return FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
807 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassInRange:
808 fragment.unoptimizedPseudoClasses.append(JSC::FunctionPtr<JSC::OperationPtrTag>(operationIsInRange));
809 return FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
810 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassIndeterminate:
811 fragment.unoptimizedPseudoClasses.append(JSC::FunctionPtr<JSC::OperationPtrTag>(operationMatchesIndeterminatePseudoClass));
812 return FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
813 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassInvalid:
814 fragment.unoptimizedPseudoClasses.append(JSC::FunctionPtr<JSC::OperationPtrTag>(operationIsInvalid));
815 return FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
816 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassOptional:
817 fragment.unoptimizedPseudoClasses.append(JSC::FunctionPtr<JSC::OperationPtrTag>(operationIsOptionalFormControl));
818 return FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
819 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassOutOfRange:
820 fragment.unoptimizedPseudoClasses.append(JSC::FunctionPtr<JSC::OperationPtrTag>(operationIsOutOfRange));
821 return FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
822 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassReadOnly:
823 fragment.unoptimizedPseudoClasses.append(JSC::FunctionPtr<JSC::OperationPtrTag>(operationMatchesReadOnlyPseudoClass));
824 return FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
825 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassReadWrite:
826 fragment.unoptimizedPseudoClasses.append(JSC::FunctionPtr<JSC::OperationPtrTag>(operationMatchesReadWritePseudoClass));
827 return FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
828 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassRequired:
829 fragment.unoptimizedPseudoClasses.append(JSC::FunctionPtr<JSC::OperationPtrTag>(operationIsRequiredFormControl));
830 return FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
831 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassValid:
832 fragment.unoptimizedPseudoClasses.append(JSC::FunctionPtr<JSC::OperationPtrTag>(operationIsValid));
833 return FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
834 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassWindowInactive:
835 fragment.unoptimizedPseudoClasses.append(JSC::FunctionPtr<JSC::OperationPtrTag>(operationIsWindowInactive));
836 return FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
837
838#if ENABLE(FULLSCREEN_API)
839 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassFullScreen:
840 fragment.unoptimizedPseudoClasses.append(JSC::FunctionPtr<JSC::OperationPtrTag>(operationMatchesFullScreenPseudoClass));
841 return FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
842 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassFullScreenDocument:
843 fragment.unoptimizedPseudoClasses.append(JSC::FunctionPtr<JSC::OperationPtrTag>(operationMatchesFullScreenDocumentPseudoClass));
844 return FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
845 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassFullScreenAncestor:
846 fragment.unoptimizedPseudoClasses.append(JSC::FunctionPtr<JSC::OperationPtrTag>(operationMatchesFullScreenAncestorPseudoClass));
847 return FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
848 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassAnimatingFullScreenTransition:
849 fragment.unoptimizedPseudoClasses.append(JSC::FunctionPtr<JSC::OperationPtrTag>(operationMatchesFullScreenAnimatingFullScreenTransitionPseudoClass));
850 return FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
851
852 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassFullScreenControlsHidden:
853 fragment.unoptimizedPseudoClasses.append(JSC::FunctionPtr<JSC::OperationPtrTag>(operationMatchesFullScreenControlsHiddenPseudoClass));
854 return FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
855#endif
856
857#if ENABLE(PICTURE_IN_PICTURE_API)
858 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassPictureInPicture:
859 fragment.unoptimizedPseudoClasses.append(JSC::FunctionPtr<JSC::OperationPtrTag>(operationMatchesPictureInPicturePseudoClass));
860 return FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
861#endif
862
863#if ENABLE(VIDEO)
864 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassFuture:
865 fragment.unoptimizedPseudoClasses.append(JSC::FunctionPtr<JSC::OperationPtrTag>(operationMatchesFutureCuePseudoClass));
866 return FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
867 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassPast:
868 fragment.unoptimizedPseudoClasses.append(JSC::FunctionPtr<JSC::OperationPtrTag>(operationMatchesPastCuePseudoClass));
869 return FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
870#endif
871
872#if ENABLE(ATTACHMENT_ELEMENT)
873 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassHasAttachment:
874 fragment.unoptimizedPseudoClasses.append(JSC::FunctionPtr<JSC::OperationPtrTag>(operationHasAttachment));
875 return FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
876#endif
877
878 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassModalDialog:
879 fragment.unoptimizedPseudoClasses.append(JSC::FunctionPtr<JSC::OperationPtrTag>(operationMatchesModalDialogPseudoClass));
880 return FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
881
882 // These pseudo-classes only have meaning with scrollbars.
883 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassHorizontal:
884 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassVertical:
885 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassDecrement:
886 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassIncrement:
887 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassStart:
888 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassEnd:
889 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassDoubleButton:
890 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassSingleButton:
891 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassNoButton:
892 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassCornerPresent:
893 return FunctionType::CannotMatchAnything;
894
895 // FIXME: Compile these pseudoclasses, too!
896 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassFirstOfType:
897 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassLastOfType:
898 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassOnlyOfType:
899 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassNthOfType:
900 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassNthLastOfType:
901 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassDrag:
902#if ENABLE(CSS_SELECTORS_LEVEL4)
903 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassDir:
904 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassRole:
905#endif
906 return FunctionType::CannotCompile;
907
908 // Optimized pseudo selectors.
909 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassAnyLink:
910 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassLink:
911 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassRoot:
912 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassTarget:
913 fragment.pseudoClasses.add(type);
914 return FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
915 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassAnyLinkDeprecated:
916 fragment.pseudoClasses.add(CSSSelector::PseudoClassAnyLink);
917 return FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
918
919 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassVisited:
920 // Determine this :visited cannot match anything statically.
921 if (!visitedMatchEnabled)
922 return FunctionType::CannotMatchAnything;
923
924 // Inside functional pseudo class except for :not, :visited never matches.
925 // And in the case inside :not, returning CannotMatchAnything indicates that :not(:visited) can match over anything.
926 if (fragmentLevel == FragmentsLevel::InFunctionalPseudoType)
927 return FunctionType::CannotMatchAnything;
928
929 fragment.pseudoClasses.add(type);
930 visitedMode = VisitedMode::Visited;
931 return FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
932
933 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassScope:
934 if (selectorContext != SelectorContext::QuerySelector) {
935 fragment.pseudoClasses.add(CSSSelector::PseudoClassRoot);
936 return FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
937 }
938 fragment.pseudoClasses.add(CSSSelector::PseudoClassScope);
939 return FunctionType::SelectorCheckerWithCheckingContext;
940
941 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassActive:
942 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassEmpty:
943 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassFirstChild:
944 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassHover:
945 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassLastChild:
946 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassOnlyChild:
947 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassPlaceholderShown:
948 fragment.pseudoClasses.add(type);
949 if (selectorContext == SelectorContext::QuerySelector)
950 return FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
951 return FunctionType::SelectorCheckerWithCheckingContext;
952
953 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassNthChild:
954 return addNthChildType(selector, selectorContext, positionInRootFragments, CSSSelector::PseudoClassFirstChild, visitedMatchEnabled, fragment.nthChildFilters, fragment.nthChildOfFilters, fragment.pseudoClasses);
955
956 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassNthLastChild:
957 return addNthChildType(selector, selectorContext, positionInRootFragments, CSSSelector::PseudoClassLastChild, visitedMatchEnabled, fragment.nthLastChildFilters, fragment.nthLastChildOfFilters, fragment.pseudoClasses);
958
959 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassNot:
960 {
961 const CSSSelectorList* selectorList = selector.selectorList();
962
963 ASSERT_WITH_MESSAGE(selectorList, "The CSS Parser should never produce valid :not() CSSSelector with an empty selectorList.");
964 if (!selectorList)
965 return FunctionType::CannotMatchAnything;
966
967 FunctionType functionType = FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
968 SelectorFragmentList* selectorFragments = nullptr;
969 for (const CSSSelector* subselector = selectorList->first(); subselector; subselector = CSSSelectorList::next(subselector)) {
970 if (!selectorFragments) {
971 fragment.notFilters.append(SelectorFragmentList());
972 selectorFragments = &fragment.notFilters.last();
973 }
974
975 VisitedMode ignoreVisitedMode = VisitedMode::None;
976 FunctionType localFunctionType = constructFragments(subselector, selectorContext, *selectorFragments, FragmentsLevel::InFunctionalPseudoType, positionInRootFragments, visitedMatchEnabled, ignoreVisitedMode, PseudoElementMatchingBehavior::NeverMatch);
977 ASSERT_WITH_MESSAGE(ignoreVisitedMode == VisitedMode::None, ":visited is disabled in the functional pseudo classes");
978
979 // Since this is not pseudo class filter, CannotMatchAnything implies this filter always passes.
980 if (localFunctionType == FunctionType::CannotMatchAnything)
981 continue;
982
983 if (localFunctionType == FunctionType::CannotCompile)
984 return FunctionType::CannotCompile;
985
986 functionType = mostRestrictiveFunctionType(functionType, localFunctionType);
987 selectorFragments = nullptr;
988 }
989
990 // If there is still a SelectorFragmentList open, the last Fragment(s) cannot match anything,
991 // we have one FragmentList too many in our selector list.
992 if (selectorFragments)
993 fragment.notFilters.removeLast();
994
995 return functionType;
996 }
997
998 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassAny:
999 {
1000 Vector<SelectorFragment, 32> anyFragments;
1001 FunctionType functionType = FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
1002 for (const CSSSelector* rootSelector = selector.selectorList()->first(); rootSelector; rootSelector = CSSSelectorList::next(rootSelector)) {
1003 SelectorFragmentList fragmentList;
1004 VisitedMode ignoreVisitedMode = VisitedMode::None;
1005 FunctionType subFunctionType = constructFragments(rootSelector, selectorContext, fragmentList, FragmentsLevel::InFunctionalPseudoType, positionInRootFragments, visitedMatchEnabled, ignoreVisitedMode, PseudoElementMatchingBehavior::NeverMatch);
1006 ASSERT_WITH_MESSAGE(ignoreVisitedMode == VisitedMode::None, ":visited is disabled in the functional pseudo classes");
1007
1008 // Since this fragment always unmatch against the element, don't insert it to anyFragments.
1009 if (subFunctionType == FunctionType::CannotMatchAnything)
1010 continue;
1011
1012 if (subFunctionType == FunctionType::CannotCompile)
1013 return FunctionType::CannotCompile;
1014
1015 // :any() may not contain complex selectors which have combinators.
1016 ASSERT(fragmentList.size() == 1);
1017 if (fragmentList.size() != 1)
1018 return FunctionType::CannotCompile;
1019
1020 const SelectorFragment& subFragment = fragmentList.first();
1021 anyFragments.append(subFragment);
1022 functionType = mostRestrictiveFunctionType(functionType, subFunctionType);
1023 }
1024
1025 // Since all fragments in :any() cannot match anything, this :any() filter cannot match anything.
1026 if (anyFragments.isEmpty())
1027 return FunctionType::CannotMatchAnything;
1028
1029 ASSERT(!anyFragments.isEmpty());
1030 fragment.anyFilters.append(anyFragments);
1031
1032 return functionType;
1033 }
1034
1035 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassLang:
1036 {
1037 const Vector<AtomString>* selectorLangArgumentList = selector.argumentList();
1038 ASSERT(selectorLangArgumentList && !selectorLangArgumentList->isEmpty());
1039 fragment.languageArgumentsList.append(selectorLangArgumentList);
1040 return FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
1041 }
1042
1043 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassIs:
1044 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassMatches:
1045 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassWhere:
1046 {
1047 SelectorList matchesList;
1048 const CSSSelectorList* selectorList = selector.selectorList();
1049 FunctionType functionType = FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
1050 SelectorFragmentList* selectorFragments = nullptr;
1051 for (const CSSSelector* subselector = selectorList->first(); subselector; subselector = CSSSelectorList::next(subselector)) {
1052 if (!selectorFragments) {
1053 matchesList.append(SelectorFragmentList());
1054 selectorFragments = &matchesList.last();
1055 }
1056
1057 VisitedMode ignoreVisitedMode = VisitedMode::None;
1058 FunctionType localFunctionType = constructFragments(subselector, selectorContext, *selectorFragments, FragmentsLevel::InFunctionalPseudoType, positionInRootFragments, visitedMatchEnabled, ignoreVisitedMode, pseudoElementMatchingBehavior);
1059 ASSERT_WITH_MESSAGE(ignoreVisitedMode == VisitedMode::None, ":visited is disabled in the functional pseudo classes");
1060
1061 // Since this fragment never matches against the element, don't insert it to matchesList.
1062 if (localFunctionType == FunctionType::CannotMatchAnything)
1063 continue;
1064
1065 if (localFunctionType == FunctionType::CannotCompile)
1066 return FunctionType::CannotCompile;
1067
1068 // FIXME: Currently pseudo elements inside :is()/:matches() are supported in non-JIT code.
1069 if (selectorFragments->first().pseudoElementSelector)
1070 return FunctionType::CannotCompile;
1071
1072 functionType = mostRestrictiveFunctionType(functionType, localFunctionType);
1073 selectorFragments = nullptr;
1074 }
1075
1076 // If there is still a SelectorFragmentList open, the last Fragment(s) cannot match anything,
1077 // we have one FragmentList too many in our selector list.
1078 if (selectorFragments)
1079 matchesList.removeLast();
1080
1081 // Since all selector list in :is()/:matches() cannot match anything, the whole :is()/:matches() filter cannot match anything.
1082 if (matchesList.isEmpty())
1083 return FunctionType::CannotMatchAnything;
1084
1085 fragment.matchesFilters.append(matchesList);
1086
1087 return functionType;
1088 }
1089 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassHost:
1090 return FunctionType::CannotCompile;
1091 case CSSSelector::PseudoClassUnknown:
1092 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1093 return FunctionType::CannotMatchAnything;
1094 }
1095
1096 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1097 return FunctionType::CannotCompile;
1098}
1099
1100inline SelectorCodeGenerator::SelectorCodeGenerator(const CSSSelector* rootSelector, SelectorContext selectorContext)
1101 : m_stackAllocator(m_assembler)
1102 , m_selectorContext(selectorContext)
1103 , m_functionType(FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker)
1104 , m_visitedMode(VisitedMode::None)
1105 , m_descendantBacktrackingStartInUse(false)
1106#if CSS_SELECTOR_JIT_DEBUGGING
1107 , m_originalSelector(rootSelector)
1108#endif
1109{
1110#if CSS_SELECTOR_JIT_DEBUGGING
1111 dataLogF("Compiling \"%s\"\n", m_originalSelector->selectorText().utf8().data());
1112#endif
1113
1114 // In QuerySelector context, :visited always has no effect due to security issues.
1115 bool visitedMatchEnabled = selectorContext != SelectorContext::QuerySelector;
1116
1117 m_functionType = constructFragments(rootSelector, m_selectorContext, m_selectorFragments, FragmentsLevel::Root, FragmentPositionInRootFragments::Rightmost, visitedMatchEnabled, m_visitedMode, PseudoElementMatchingBehavior::CanMatch);
1118 if (m_functionType != FunctionType::CannotCompile && m_functionType != FunctionType::CannotMatchAnything)
1119 computeBacktrackingInformation(m_selectorFragments);
1120}
1121
1122static bool pseudoClassOnlyMatchesLinksInQuirksMode(const CSSSelector& selector)
1123{
1124 CSSSelector::PseudoClassType pseudoClassType = selector.pseudoClassType();
1125 return pseudoClassType == CSSSelector::PseudoClassHover || pseudoClassType == CSSSelector::PseudoClassActive;
1126}
1127
1128static bool isScrollbarPseudoElement(CSSSelector::PseudoElementType type)
1129{
1130 return type >= CSSSelector::PseudoElementScrollbar && type <= CSSSelector::PseudoElementScrollbarTrackPiece;
1131}
1132
1133static FunctionType constructFragmentsInternal(const CSSSelector* rootSelector, SelectorContext selectorContext, SelectorFragmentList& selectorFragments, FragmentsLevel fragmentLevel, FragmentPositionInRootFragments positionInRootFragments, bool visitedMatchEnabled, VisitedMode& visitedMode, PseudoElementMatchingBehavior pseudoElementMatchingBehavior)
1134{
1135 FragmentRelation relationToPreviousFragment = FragmentRelation::Rightmost;
1136 bool isRightmostOrAdjacent = positionInRootFragments != FragmentPositionInRootFragments::Other;
1137 FunctionType functionType = FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
1138 SelectorFragment* fragment = nullptr;
1139 for (const CSSSelector* selector = rootSelector; selector; selector = selector->tagHistory()) {
1140 if (!fragment) {
1141 selectorFragments.append(SelectorFragment());
1142 fragment = &selectorFragments.last();
1143 }
1144
1145 // A selector is invalid if something follows a pseudo-element.
1146 // We make an exception for scrollbar pseudo elements and allow a set of pseudo classes (but nothing else)
1147 // to follow the pseudo elements.
1148 if (fragment->pseudoElementSelector && !isScrollbarPseudoElement(fragment->pseudoElementSelector->pseudoElementType()))
1149 return FunctionType::CannotMatchAnything;
1150
1151 switch (selector->match()) {
1152 case CSSSelector::Tag:
1153 ASSERT(!fragment->tagNameSelector);
1154 fragment->tagNameSelector = selector;
1155 if (fragment->tagNameSelector->tagQName() != anyQName())
1156 fragment->onlyMatchesLinksInQuirksMode = false;
1157 break;
1158 case CSSSelector::Id: {
1159 const AtomString& id = selector->value();
1160 if (fragment->id) {
1161 if (id != *fragment->id)
1162 return FunctionType::CannotMatchAnything;
1163 } else
1164 fragment->id = &(selector->value());
1165 fragment->onlyMatchesLinksInQuirksMode = false;
1166 break;
1167 }
1168 case CSSSelector::Class:
1169 fragment->classNames.append(selector->value().impl());
1170 fragment->onlyMatchesLinksInQuirksMode = false;
1171 break;
1172 case CSSSelector::PseudoClass: {
1173 FragmentPositionInRootFragments subPosition = positionInRootFragments;
1174 if (relationToPreviousFragment != FragmentRelation::Rightmost)
1175 subPosition = isRightmostOrAdjacent ? FragmentPositionInRootFragments::AdjacentToRightmost : FragmentPositionInRootFragments::Other;
1176 if (fragment->pseudoElementSelector && isScrollbarPseudoElement(fragment->pseudoElementSelector->pseudoElementType()))
1177 functionType = mostRestrictiveFunctionType(functionType, addScrollbarPseudoClassType(*selector, *fragment));
1178 else {
1179 functionType = mostRestrictiveFunctionType(functionType, addPseudoClassType(*selector, *fragment, selectorContext, fragmentLevel, subPosition, visitedMatchEnabled, visitedMode, pseudoElementMatchingBehavior));
1180 }
1181 if (!pseudoClassOnlyMatchesLinksInQuirksMode(*selector))
1182 fragment->onlyMatchesLinksInQuirksMode = false;
1183 if (functionType == FunctionType::CannotCompile || functionType == FunctionType::CannotMatchAnything)
1184 return functionType;
1185 break;
1186 }
1187 case CSSSelector::PseudoElement: {
1188 fragment->onlyMatchesLinksInQuirksMode = false;
1189
1190 // In the QuerySelector context, PseudoElement selectors always fail.
1191 if (selectorContext == SelectorContext::QuerySelector)
1192 return FunctionType::CannotMatchAnything;
1193
1194 switch (selector->pseudoElementType()) {
1195 case CSSSelector::PseudoElementAfter:
1196 case CSSSelector::PseudoElementBefore:
1197 case CSSSelector::PseudoElementFirstLetter:
1198 case CSSSelector::PseudoElementFirstLine:
1199 case CSSSelector::PseudoElementScrollbar:
1200 case CSSSelector::PseudoElementScrollbarButton:
1201 case CSSSelector::PseudoElementScrollbarCorner:
1202 case CSSSelector::PseudoElementScrollbarThumb:
1203 case CSSSelector::PseudoElementScrollbarTrack:
1204 case CSSSelector::PseudoElementScrollbarTrackPiece:
1205 ASSERT(!fragment->pseudoElementSelector);
1206 fragment->pseudoElementSelector = selector;
1207 break;
1208 case CSSSelector::PseudoElementUnknown:
1209 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1210 return FunctionType::CannotMatchAnything;
1211 // FIXME: Support PseudoId::Resizer, PseudoId::Selection etc.
1212 default:
1213 // This branch includes custom pseudo elements.
1214 return FunctionType::CannotCompile;
1215 }
1216
1217 if (pseudoElementMatchingBehavior == PseudoElementMatchingBehavior::NeverMatch)
1218 return FunctionType::CannotMatchAnything;
1219
1220 functionType = FunctionType::SelectorCheckerWithCheckingContext;
1221 break;
1222 }
1223 case CSSSelector::List:
1224 if (selector->value().find(isHTMLSpace<UChar>) != notFound)
1225 return FunctionType::CannotMatchAnything;
1226 FALLTHROUGH;
1227 case CSSSelector::Begin:
1228 case CSSSelector::End:
1229 case CSSSelector::Contain:
1230 if (selector->value().isEmpty())
1231 return FunctionType::CannotMatchAnything;
1232 FALLTHROUGH;
1233 case CSSSelector::Exact:
1234 case CSSSelector::Hyphen:
1235 fragment->onlyMatchesLinksInQuirksMode = false;
1236 fragment->attributes.append(AttributeMatchingInfo(*selector));
1237 break;
1238
1239 case CSSSelector::Set:
1240 fragment->onlyMatchesLinksInQuirksMode = false;
1241 fragment->attributes.append(AttributeMatchingInfo(*selector));
1242 break;
1243 case CSSSelector::PagePseudoClass:
1244 fragment->onlyMatchesLinksInQuirksMode = false;
1245 // Pseudo page class are only relevant for style resolution, they are ignored for matching.
1246 break;
1247 case CSSSelector::Unknown:
1248 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1249 return FunctionType::CannotMatchAnything;
1250 }
1251
1252 auto relation = selector->relation();
1253 if (relation == CSSSelector::Subselector)
1254 continue;
1255
1256 if (relation == CSSSelector::ShadowDescendant && !selector->isLastInTagHistory())
1257 return FunctionType::CannotCompile;
1258
1259 if (relation == CSSSelector::DirectAdjacent || relation == CSSSelector::IndirectAdjacent) {
1260 FunctionType relationFunctionType = FunctionType::SelectorCheckerWithCheckingContext;
1261 if (selectorContext == SelectorContext::QuerySelector)
1262 relationFunctionType = FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker;
1263 functionType = mostRestrictiveFunctionType(functionType, relationFunctionType);
1264
1265 // When the relation is adjacent, disable :visited match.
1266 visitedMatchEnabled = false;
1267 }
1268
1269 // Virtual pseudo element is only effective in the rightmost fragment.
1270 pseudoElementMatchingBehavior = PseudoElementMatchingBehavior::NeverMatch;
1271
1272 fragment->relationToLeftFragment = fragmentRelationForSelectorRelation(relation);
1273 fragment->relationToRightFragment = relationToPreviousFragment;
1274 fragment->positionInRootFragments = positionInRootFragments;
1275 fragment->isRightmostOrAdjacent = isRightmostOrAdjacent;
1276 relationToPreviousFragment = fragment->relationToLeftFragment;
1277 if (relationToPreviousFragment != FragmentRelation::Rightmost && relationToPreviousFragment != FragmentRelation::DirectAdjacent && relationToPreviousFragment != FragmentRelation::IndirectAdjacent)
1278 isRightmostOrAdjacent = false;
1279
1280 if (fragmentLevel != FragmentsLevel::Root)
1281 fragment->onlyMatchesLinksInQuirksMode = false;
1282
1283 fragment = nullptr;
1284 }
1285
1286 ASSERT(!fragment);
1287
1288 selectorFragments.staticSpecificity = rootSelector->computeSpecificity();
1289
1290 return functionType;
1291}
1292
1293static FunctionType constructFragments(const CSSSelector* rootSelector, SelectorContext selectorContext, SelectorFragmentList& selectorFragments, FragmentsLevel fragmentLevel, FragmentPositionInRootFragments positionInRootFragments, bool visitedMatchEnabled, VisitedMode& visitedMode, PseudoElementMatchingBehavior pseudoElementMatchingBehavior)
1294{
1295 ASSERT(selectorFragments.isEmpty());
1296
1297 FunctionType functionType = constructFragmentsInternal(rootSelector, selectorContext, selectorFragments, fragmentLevel, positionInRootFragments, visitedMatchEnabled, visitedMode, pseudoElementMatchingBehavior);
1298 if (functionType != FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker && functionType != FunctionType::SelectorCheckerWithCheckingContext)
1299 selectorFragments.clear();
1300 return functionType;
1301}
1302
1303static inline bool attributeNameTestingRequiresNamespaceRegister(const CSSSelector& attributeSelector)
1304{
1305 return attributeSelector.attribute().prefix() != starAtom() && !attributeSelector.attribute().namespaceURI().isNull();
1306}
1307
1308static inline bool attributeValueTestingRequiresExtraRegister(const AttributeMatchingInfo& attributeInfo)
1309{
1310 switch (attributeInfo.attributeCaseSensitivity()) {
1311 case AttributeCaseSensitivity::CaseSensitive:
1312 return false;
1313 case AttributeCaseSensitivity::HTMLLegacyCaseInsensitive:
1314 return true;
1315 case AttributeCaseSensitivity::CaseInsensitive:
1316 return attributeInfo.selector().match() == CSSSelector::Exact;
1317 }
1318 return true;
1319}
1320
1321// Element + ElementData + a pointer to values + an index on that pointer + the value we expect;
1322static const unsigned minimumRequiredRegisterCount = 5;
1323// Element + ElementData + scratchRegister + attributeArrayPointer + expectedLocalName + (qualifiedNameImpl && expectedValue).
1324static const unsigned minimumRequiredRegisterCountForAttributeFilter = 6;
1325// On x86, we always need 6 registers: Element + SiblingCounter + SiblingCounterCopy + divisor + dividend + remainder.
1326// On other architectures, we need 6 registers for style resolution:
1327// Element + elementCounter + previousSibling + checkingContext + lastRelation + nextSiblingElement.
1328static const unsigned minimumRequiredRegisterCountForNthChildFilter = 6;
1329
1330static unsigned minimumRegisterRequirements(const SelectorFragment& selectorFragment)
1331{
1332 unsigned minimum = minimumRequiredRegisterCount;
1333 const auto& attributes = selectorFragment.attributes;
1334
1335 // Attributes cause some register pressure.
1336 unsigned attributeCount = attributes.size();
1337 for (unsigned attributeIndex = 0; attributeIndex < attributeCount; ++attributeIndex) {
1338 unsigned attributeMinimum = minimumRequiredRegisterCountForAttributeFilter;
1339
1340 if (attributeIndex + 1 < attributeCount)
1341 attributeMinimum += 2; // For the local copy of the counter and attributeArrayPointer.
1342
1343 const AttributeMatchingInfo& attributeInfo = attributes[attributeIndex];
1344 const CSSSelector& attributeSelector = attributeInfo.selector();
1345 if (attributeNameTestingRequiresNamespaceRegister(attributeSelector)
1346 || attributeValueTestingRequiresExtraRegister(attributeInfo))
1347 attributeMinimum += 1;
1348
1349 minimum = std::max(minimum, attributeMinimum);
1350 }
1351
1352 if (!selectorFragment.nthChildFilters.isEmpty() || !selectorFragment.nthChildOfFilters.isEmpty() || !selectorFragment.nthLastChildFilters.isEmpty() || !selectorFragment.nthLastChildOfFilters.isEmpty())
1353 minimum = std::max(minimum, minimumRequiredRegisterCountForNthChildFilter);
1354
1355 // :any pseudo class filters cause some register pressure.
1356 for (const auto& subFragments : selectorFragment.anyFilters) {
1357 for (const SelectorFragment& subFragment : subFragments) {
1358 unsigned anyFilterMinimum = minimumRegisterRequirements(subFragment);
1359 minimum = std::max(minimum, anyFilterMinimum);
1360 }
1361 }
1362
1363 return minimum;
1364}
1365
1366bool hasAnyCombinators(const Vector<SelectorFragmentList>& selectorList);
1367template <size_t inlineCapacity>
1368bool hasAnyCombinators(const Vector<SelectorFragment, inlineCapacity>& selectorFragmentList);
1369
1370bool hasAnyCombinators(const Vector<SelectorFragmentList>& selectorList)
1371{
1372 for (const SelectorFragmentList& selectorFragmentList : selectorList) {
1373 if (hasAnyCombinators(selectorFragmentList))
1374 return true;
1375 }
1376 return false;
1377}
1378
1379template <size_t inlineCapacity>
1380bool hasAnyCombinators(const Vector<SelectorFragment, inlineCapacity>& selectorFragmentList)
1381{
1382 if (selectorFragmentList.isEmpty())
1383 return false;
1384 if (selectorFragmentList.size() != 1)
1385 return true;
1386 if (hasAnyCombinators(selectorFragmentList.first().notFilters))
1387 return true;
1388 for (const SelectorList& matchesList : selectorFragmentList.first().matchesFilters) {
1389 if (hasAnyCombinators(matchesList))
1390 return true;
1391 }
1392 for (const NthChildOfSelectorInfo& nthChildOfSelectorInfo : selectorFragmentList.first().nthChildOfFilters) {
1393 if (hasAnyCombinators(nthChildOfSelectorInfo.selectorList))
1394 return true;
1395 }
1396 for (const NthChildOfSelectorInfo& nthLastChildOfSelectorInfo : selectorFragmentList.first().nthLastChildOfFilters) {
1397 if (hasAnyCombinators(nthLastChildOfSelectorInfo.selectorList))
1398 return true;
1399 }
1400 return false;
1401}
1402
1403// The CSS JIT has only been validated with a strict minimum of 6 allocated registers.
1404const unsigned minimumRegisterRequirement = 6;
1405
1406void computeBacktrackingMemoryRequirements(SelectorFragmentList& selectorFragments, bool backtrackingRegisterReserved = false);
1407
1408static void computeBacktrackingMemoryRequirements(SelectorList& selectorList, unsigned& totalRegisterRequirements, unsigned& totalStackRequirements, bool backtrackingRegisterReservedForFragment = false)
1409{
1410 unsigned selectorListRegisterRequirements = 0;
1411 unsigned selectorListStackRequirements = 0;
1412 bool clobberElementAddressRegister = false;
1413
1414 for (SelectorFragmentList& selectorFragmentList : selectorList) {
1415 computeBacktrackingMemoryRequirements(selectorFragmentList, backtrackingRegisterReservedForFragment);
1416
1417 selectorListRegisterRequirements = std::max(selectorListRegisterRequirements, selectorFragmentList.registerRequirements);
1418 selectorListStackRequirements = std::max(selectorListStackRequirements, selectorFragmentList.stackRequirements);
1419 clobberElementAddressRegister = clobberElementAddressRegister || selectorFragmentList.clobberElementAddressRegister;
1420 }
1421
1422 totalRegisterRequirements = std::max(totalRegisterRequirements, selectorListRegisterRequirements);
1423 totalStackRequirements = std::max(totalStackRequirements, selectorListStackRequirements);
1424
1425 selectorList.registerRequirements = std::max(selectorListRegisterRequirements, minimumRegisterRequirement);
1426 selectorList.stackRequirements = selectorListStackRequirements;
1427 selectorList.clobberElementAddressRegister = clobberElementAddressRegister;
1428}
1429
1430void computeBacktrackingMemoryRequirements(SelectorFragmentList& selectorFragments, bool backtrackingRegisterReserved)
1431{
1432 selectorFragments.registerRequirements = minimumRegisterRequirement;
1433 selectorFragments.stackRequirements = 0;
1434 selectorFragments.clobberElementAddressRegister = hasAnyCombinators(selectorFragments);
1435
1436 for (SelectorFragment& selectorFragment : selectorFragments) {
1437 unsigned fragmentRegisterRequirements = minimumRegisterRequirements(selectorFragment);
1438 unsigned fragmentStackRequirements = 0;
1439
1440 bool backtrackingRegisterReservedForFragment = backtrackingRegisterReserved || selectorFragment.backtrackingFlags & BacktrackingFlag::InChainWithDescendantTail;
1441
1442 computeBacktrackingMemoryRequirements(selectorFragment.notFilters, fragmentRegisterRequirements, fragmentStackRequirements, backtrackingRegisterReservedForFragment);
1443
1444 for (SelectorList& matchesList : selectorFragment.matchesFilters)
1445 computeBacktrackingMemoryRequirements(matchesList, fragmentRegisterRequirements, fragmentStackRequirements, backtrackingRegisterReservedForFragment);
1446
1447 for (NthChildOfSelectorInfo& nthChildOfSelectorInfo : selectorFragment.nthChildOfFilters)
1448 computeBacktrackingMemoryRequirements(nthChildOfSelectorInfo.selectorList, fragmentRegisterRequirements, fragmentStackRequirements, backtrackingRegisterReservedForFragment);
1449
1450 for (NthChildOfSelectorInfo& nthLastChildOfSelectorInfo : selectorFragment.nthLastChildOfFilters)
1451 computeBacktrackingMemoryRequirements(nthLastChildOfSelectorInfo.selectorList, fragmentRegisterRequirements, fragmentStackRequirements, backtrackingRegisterReservedForFragment);
1452
1453 if (selectorFragment.backtrackingFlags & BacktrackingFlag::InChainWithDescendantTail) {
1454 if (!backtrackingRegisterReserved)
1455 ++fragmentRegisterRequirements;
1456 else
1457 ++fragmentStackRequirements;
1458 }
1459 if (selectorFragment.backtrackingFlags & BacktrackingFlag::InChainWithAdjacentTail)
1460 ++fragmentStackRequirements;
1461
1462 selectorFragments.registerRequirements = std::max(selectorFragments.registerRequirements, fragmentRegisterRequirements);
1463 selectorFragments.stackRequirements = std::max(selectorFragments.stackRequirements, fragmentStackRequirements);
1464 }
1465}
1466
1467inline SelectorCompilationStatus SelectorCodeGenerator::compile(JSC::MacroAssemblerCodeRef<JSC::CSSSelectorPtrTag>& codeRef)
1468{
1469 switch (m_functionType) {
1470 case FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker:
1471 case FunctionType::SelectorCheckerWithCheckingContext:
1472 generateSelectorChecker();
1473 break;
1474 case FunctionType::CannotMatchAnything:
1475 if (!JSC::Options::useJITCage())
1476 m_assembler.tagReturnAddress();
1477 m_assembler.move(Assembler::TrustedImm32(0), returnRegister);
1478 generateReturn();
1479 break;
1480 case FunctionType::CannotCompile:
1481 return SelectorCompilationStatus::CannotCompile;
1482 }
1483
1484 JSC::LinkBuffer linkBuffer(m_assembler, CSS_CODE_ID, JSC::LinkBuffer::Profile::CSSJIT, JSC::JITCompilationCanFail);
1485 if (!linkBuffer.isValid()) {
1486 // This could be SelectorCompilationStatus::NotCompiled but that would cause us to re-enter
1487 // the CSS JIT every time we evaluate that selector.
1488 // If we failed to allocate the buffer, we have bigger problems than CSS performance, it is fine
1489 // to be slower.
1490 return SelectorCompilationStatus::CannotCompile;
1491 }
1492
1493 for (unsigned i = 0; i < m_functionCalls.size(); i++)
1494 linkBuffer.link(m_functionCalls[i].first, m_functionCalls[i].second);
1495
1496#if CSS_SELECTOR_JIT_DEBUGGING
1497 codeRef = linkBuffer.finalizeCodeWithDisassembly(JSC::CSSSelectorPtrTag, "CSS Selector JIT for \"%s\"", m_originalSelector->selectorText().utf8().data());
1498#else
1499 codeRef = FINALIZE_CODE(linkBuffer, JSC::CSSSelectorPtrTag, "CSS Selector JIT");
1500#endif
1501
1502 if (m_functionType == FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker || m_functionType == FunctionType::CannotMatchAnything)
1503 return SelectorCompilationStatus::SimpleSelectorChecker;
1504 return SelectorCompilationStatus::SelectorCheckerWithCheckingContext;
1505}
1506
1507
1508static inline void updateChainStates(const SelectorFragment& fragment, bool& hasDescendantRelationOnTheRight, unsigned& ancestorPositionSinceDescendantRelation, bool& hasIndirectAdjacentRelationOnTheRightOfDirectAdjacentChain, unsigned& adjacentPositionSinceIndirectAdjacentTreeWalk)
1509{
1510 switch (fragment.relationToRightFragment) {
1511 case FragmentRelation::Rightmost:
1512 break;
1513 case FragmentRelation::Descendant:
1514 hasDescendantRelationOnTheRight = true;
1515 ancestorPositionSinceDescendantRelation = 0;
1516 hasIndirectAdjacentRelationOnTheRightOfDirectAdjacentChain = false;
1517 break;
1518 case FragmentRelation::Child:
1519 if (hasDescendantRelationOnTheRight)
1520 ++ancestorPositionSinceDescendantRelation;
1521 hasIndirectAdjacentRelationOnTheRightOfDirectAdjacentChain = false;
1522 break;
1523 case FragmentRelation::DirectAdjacent:
1524 if (hasIndirectAdjacentRelationOnTheRightOfDirectAdjacentChain)
1525 ++adjacentPositionSinceIndirectAdjacentTreeWalk;
1526 break;
1527 case FragmentRelation::IndirectAdjacent:
1528 hasIndirectAdjacentRelationOnTheRightOfDirectAdjacentChain = true;
1529 adjacentPositionSinceIndirectAdjacentTreeWalk = 0;
1530 break;
1531 }
1532}
1533
1534static inline bool isFirstAncestor(unsigned ancestorPositionSinceDescendantRelation)
1535{
1536 return ancestorPositionSinceDescendantRelation == 1;
1537}
1538
1539static inline bool isFirstAdjacent(unsigned adjacentPositionSinceIndirectAdjacentTreeWalk)
1540{
1541 return adjacentPositionSinceIndirectAdjacentTreeWalk == 1;
1542}
1543
1544static inline BacktrackingAction solveDescendantBacktrackingActionForChild(const SelectorFragment& fragment, unsigned backtrackingStartHeightFromDescendant)
1545{
1546 // If height is invalid (e.g. There's no tag name).
1547 if (backtrackingStartHeightFromDescendant == invalidHeight)
1548 return BacktrackingAction::NoBacktracking;
1549
1550 // Start backtracking from the current element.
1551 if (backtrackingStartHeightFromDescendant == fragment.heightFromDescendant)
1552 return BacktrackingAction::JumpToDescendantEntryPoint;
1553
1554 // Start backtracking from the parent of current element.
1555 if (backtrackingStartHeightFromDescendant == (fragment.heightFromDescendant + 1))
1556 return BacktrackingAction::JumpToDescendantTreeWalkerEntryPoint;
1557
1558 return BacktrackingAction::JumpToDescendantTail;
1559}
1560
1561static inline BacktrackingAction solveAdjacentBacktrackingActionForDirectAdjacent(const SelectorFragment& fragment, unsigned backtrackingStartWidthFromIndirectAdjacent)
1562{
1563 // If width is invalid (e.g. There's no tag name).
1564 if (backtrackingStartWidthFromIndirectAdjacent == invalidWidth)
1565 return BacktrackingAction::NoBacktracking;
1566
1567 // Start backtracking from the current element.
1568 if (backtrackingStartWidthFromIndirectAdjacent == fragment.widthFromIndirectAdjacent)
1569 return BacktrackingAction::JumpToIndirectAdjacentEntryPoint;
1570
1571 // Start backtracking from the previous adjacent of current element.
1572 if (backtrackingStartWidthFromIndirectAdjacent == (fragment.widthFromIndirectAdjacent + 1))
1573 return BacktrackingAction::JumpToIndirectAdjacentTreeWalkerEntryPoint;
1574
1575 return BacktrackingAction::JumpToDirectAdjacentTail;
1576}
1577
1578static inline BacktrackingAction solveAdjacentTraversalBacktrackingAction(const SelectorFragment& fragment, bool hasDescendantRelationOnTheRight)
1579{
1580 if (!hasDescendantRelationOnTheRight)
1581 return BacktrackingAction::NoBacktracking;
1582
1583 if (fragment.tagNameMatchedBacktrackingStartHeightFromDescendant == (fragment.heightFromDescendant + 1))
1584 return BacktrackingAction::JumpToDescendantTreeWalkerEntryPoint;
1585
1586 return BacktrackingAction::JumpToDescendantTail;
1587}
1588
1589static inline void solveBacktrackingAction(SelectorFragment& fragment, bool hasDescendantRelationOnTheRight, bool hasIndirectAdjacentRelationOnTheRightOfDirectAdjacentChain)
1590{
1591 switch (fragment.relationToRightFragment) {
1592 case FragmentRelation::Rightmost:
1593 case FragmentRelation::Descendant:
1594 break;
1595 case FragmentRelation::Child:
1596 // Failure to match the element should resume matching at the nearest ancestor/descendant entry point.
1597 if (hasDescendantRelationOnTheRight) {
1598 fragment.matchingTagNameBacktrackingAction = solveDescendantBacktrackingActionForChild(fragment, fragment.tagNameNotMatchedBacktrackingStartHeightFromDescendant);
1599 fragment.matchingPostTagNameBacktrackingAction = solveDescendantBacktrackingActionForChild(fragment, fragment.tagNameMatchedBacktrackingStartHeightFromDescendant);
1600 }
1601 break;
1602 case FragmentRelation::DirectAdjacent:
1603 // Failure on traversal implies no other sibling traversal can match. Matching should resume at the
1604 // nearest ancestor/descendant traversal.
1605 fragment.traversalBacktrackingAction = solveAdjacentTraversalBacktrackingAction(fragment, hasDescendantRelationOnTheRight);
1606
1607 // If the rightmost relation is a indirect adjacent, matching sould resume from there.
1608 // Otherwise, we resume from the latest ancestor/descendant if any.
1609 if (hasIndirectAdjacentRelationOnTheRightOfDirectAdjacentChain) {
1610 fragment.matchingTagNameBacktrackingAction = solveAdjacentBacktrackingActionForDirectAdjacent(fragment, fragment.tagNameNotMatchedBacktrackingStartWidthFromIndirectAdjacent);
1611 fragment.matchingPostTagNameBacktrackingAction = solveAdjacentBacktrackingActionForDirectAdjacent(fragment, fragment.tagNameMatchedBacktrackingStartWidthFromIndirectAdjacent);
1612 } else if (hasDescendantRelationOnTheRight) {
1613 // Since we resume from the latest ancestor/descendant, the action is the same as the traversal action.
1614 fragment.matchingTagNameBacktrackingAction = fragment.traversalBacktrackingAction;
1615 fragment.matchingPostTagNameBacktrackingAction = fragment.traversalBacktrackingAction;
1616 }
1617 break;
1618 case FragmentRelation::IndirectAdjacent:
1619 // Failure on traversal implies no other sibling matching will succeed. Matching can resume
1620 // from the latest ancestor/descendant.
1621 fragment.traversalBacktrackingAction = solveAdjacentTraversalBacktrackingAction(fragment, hasDescendantRelationOnTheRight);
1622 break;
1623 }
1624}
1625
1626enum class TagNameEquality {
1627 StrictlyNotEqual,
1628 MaybeEqual,
1629 StrictlyEqual
1630};
1631
1632static inline TagNameEquality equalTagNames(const CSSSelector* lhs, const CSSSelector* rhs)
1633{
1634 if (!lhs || !rhs)
1635 return TagNameEquality::MaybeEqual;
1636
1637 const QualifiedName& lhsQualifiedName = lhs->tagQName();
1638 if (lhsQualifiedName == anyQName())
1639 return TagNameEquality::MaybeEqual;
1640
1641 const QualifiedName& rhsQualifiedName = rhs->tagQName();
1642 if (rhsQualifiedName == anyQName())
1643 return TagNameEquality::MaybeEqual;
1644
1645 const AtomString& lhsLocalName = lhsQualifiedName.localName();
1646 const AtomString& rhsLocalName = rhsQualifiedName.localName();
1647 if (lhsLocalName != starAtom() && rhsLocalName != starAtom()) {
1648 const AtomString& lhsLowercaseLocalName = lhs->tagLowercaseLocalName();
1649 const AtomString& rhsLowercaseLocalName = rhs->tagLowercaseLocalName();
1650
1651 if (lhsLowercaseLocalName != rhsLowercaseLocalName)
1652 return TagNameEquality::StrictlyNotEqual;
1653
1654 if (lhsLocalName == lhsLowercaseLocalName && rhsLocalName == rhsLowercaseLocalName)
1655 return TagNameEquality::StrictlyEqual;
1656 return TagNameEquality::MaybeEqual;
1657 }
1658
1659 const AtomString& lhsNamespaceURI = lhsQualifiedName.namespaceURI();
1660 const AtomString& rhsNamespaceURI = rhsQualifiedName.namespaceURI();
1661 if (lhsNamespaceURI != starAtom() && rhsNamespaceURI != starAtom()) {
1662 if (lhsNamespaceURI != rhsNamespaceURI)
1663 return TagNameEquality::StrictlyNotEqual;
1664 return TagNameEquality::StrictlyEqual;
1665 }
1666
1667 return TagNameEquality::MaybeEqual;
1668}
1669
1670static inline bool equalTagNamePatterns(const TagNamePattern& lhs, const TagNamePattern& rhs)
1671{
1672 TagNameEquality result = equalTagNames(lhs.tagNameSelector, rhs.tagNameSelector);
1673 if (result == TagNameEquality::MaybeEqual)
1674 return true;
1675
1676 // If both rhs & lhs have actual localName (or NamespaceURI),
1677 // TagNameEquality result becomes StrictlyEqual or StrictlyNotEqual Since inverted lhs never matches on rhs.
1678 bool equal = result == TagNameEquality::StrictlyEqual;
1679 if (lhs.inverted)
1680 return !equal;
1681 return equal;
1682}
1683
1684// Find the largest matching prefix from already known tagNames.
1685// And by using this, compute an appropriate height of backtracking start element from the closest base element in the chain.
1686static inline unsigned computeBacktrackingStartOffsetInChain(const TagNameList& tagNames, unsigned maxPrefixSize)
1687{
1688 RELEASE_ASSERT(!tagNames.isEmpty());
1689 RELEASE_ASSERT(maxPrefixSize < tagNames.size());
1690
1691 for (unsigned largestPrefixSize = maxPrefixSize; largestPrefixSize > 0; --largestPrefixSize) {
1692 unsigned offsetToLargestPrefix = tagNames.size() - largestPrefixSize;
1693 bool matched = true;
1694 // Since TagNamePatterns are pushed to a tagNames, check tagNames with reverse order.
1695 for (unsigned i = 0; i < largestPrefixSize; ++i) {
1696 unsigned lastIndex = tagNames.size() - 1;
1697 unsigned currentIndex = lastIndex - i;
1698 if (!equalTagNamePatterns(tagNames[currentIndex], tagNames[currentIndex - offsetToLargestPrefix])) {
1699 matched = false;
1700 break;
1701 }
1702 }
1703 if (matched)
1704 return offsetToLargestPrefix;
1705 }
1706 return tagNames.size();
1707}
1708
1709static inline void computeBacktrackingHeightFromDescendant(SelectorFragment& fragment, TagNameList& tagNamesForChildChain, bool hasDescendantRelationOnTheRight, const SelectorFragment*& previousChildFragmentInChildChain)
1710{
1711 if (!hasDescendantRelationOnTheRight)
1712 return;
1713
1714 if (fragment.relationToRightFragment == FragmentRelation::Descendant) {
1715 tagNamesForChildChain.clear();
1716
1717 TagNamePattern pattern;
1718 pattern.tagNameSelector = fragment.tagNameSelector;
1719 tagNamesForChildChain.append(pattern);
1720 fragment.heightFromDescendant = 0;
1721 previousChildFragmentInChildChain = nullptr;
1722 } else if (fragment.relationToRightFragment == FragmentRelation::Child) {
1723 TagNamePattern pattern;
1724 pattern.tagNameSelector = fragment.tagNameSelector;
1725 tagNamesForChildChain.append(pattern);
1726
1727 unsigned maxPrefixSize = tagNamesForChildChain.size() - 1;
1728 if (previousChildFragmentInChildChain) {
1729 RELEASE_ASSERT(tagNamesForChildChain.size() >= previousChildFragmentInChildChain->tagNameMatchedBacktrackingStartHeightFromDescendant);
1730 maxPrefixSize = tagNamesForChildChain.size() - previousChildFragmentInChildChain->tagNameMatchedBacktrackingStartHeightFromDescendant;
1731 }
1732
1733 if (pattern.tagNameSelector) {
1734 // Compute height from descendant in the case that tagName is not matched.
1735 tagNamesForChildChain.last().inverted = true;
1736 fragment.tagNameNotMatchedBacktrackingStartHeightFromDescendant = computeBacktrackingStartOffsetInChain(tagNamesForChildChain, maxPrefixSize);
1737 }
1738
1739 // Compute height from descendant in the case that tagName is matched.
1740 tagNamesForChildChain.last().inverted = false;
1741 fragment.tagNameMatchedBacktrackingStartHeightFromDescendant = computeBacktrackingStartOffsetInChain(tagNamesForChildChain, maxPrefixSize);
1742 fragment.heightFromDescendant = tagNamesForChildChain.size() - 1;
1743 previousChildFragmentInChildChain = &fragment;
1744 } else {
1745 if (previousChildFragmentInChildChain) {
1746 fragment.tagNameNotMatchedBacktrackingStartHeightFromDescendant = previousChildFragmentInChildChain->tagNameNotMatchedBacktrackingStartHeightFromDescendant;
1747 fragment.tagNameMatchedBacktrackingStartHeightFromDescendant = previousChildFragmentInChildChain->tagNameMatchedBacktrackingStartHeightFromDescendant;
1748 fragment.heightFromDescendant = previousChildFragmentInChildChain->heightFromDescendant;
1749 } else {
1750 fragment.tagNameNotMatchedBacktrackingStartHeightFromDescendant = tagNamesForChildChain.size();
1751 fragment.tagNameMatchedBacktrackingStartHeightFromDescendant = tagNamesForChildChain.size();
1752 fragment.heightFromDescendant = 0;
1753 }
1754 }
1755}
1756
1757static inline void computeBacktrackingWidthFromIndirectAdjacent(SelectorFragment& fragment, TagNameList& tagNamesForDirectAdjacentChain, bool hasIndirectAdjacentRelationOnTheRightOfDirectAdjacentChain, const SelectorFragment*& previousDirectAdjacentFragmentInDirectAdjacentChain)
1758{
1759 if (!hasIndirectAdjacentRelationOnTheRightOfDirectAdjacentChain)
1760 return;
1761
1762 if (fragment.relationToRightFragment == FragmentRelation::IndirectAdjacent) {
1763 tagNamesForDirectAdjacentChain.clear();
1764
1765 TagNamePattern pattern;
1766 pattern.tagNameSelector = fragment.tagNameSelector;
1767 tagNamesForDirectAdjacentChain.append(pattern);
1768 fragment.widthFromIndirectAdjacent = 0;
1769 previousDirectAdjacentFragmentInDirectAdjacentChain = nullptr;
1770 } else if (fragment.relationToRightFragment == FragmentRelation::DirectAdjacent) {
1771 TagNamePattern pattern;
1772 pattern.tagNameSelector = fragment.tagNameSelector;
1773 tagNamesForDirectAdjacentChain.append(pattern);
1774
1775 unsigned maxPrefixSize = tagNamesForDirectAdjacentChain.size() - 1;
1776 if (previousDirectAdjacentFragmentInDirectAdjacentChain) {
1777 RELEASE_ASSERT(tagNamesForDirectAdjacentChain.size() >= previousDirectAdjacentFragmentInDirectAdjacentChain->tagNameMatchedBacktrackingStartWidthFromIndirectAdjacent);
1778 maxPrefixSize = tagNamesForDirectAdjacentChain.size() - previousDirectAdjacentFragmentInDirectAdjacentChain->tagNameMatchedBacktrackingStartWidthFromIndirectAdjacent;
1779 }
1780
1781 if (pattern.tagNameSelector) {
1782 // Compute height from descendant in the case that tagName is not matched.
1783 tagNamesForDirectAdjacentChain.last().inverted = true;
1784 fragment.tagNameNotMatchedBacktrackingStartWidthFromIndirectAdjacent = computeBacktrackingStartOffsetInChain(tagNamesForDirectAdjacentChain, maxPrefixSize);
1785 }
1786
1787 // Compute height from descendant in the case that tagName is matched.
1788 tagNamesForDirectAdjacentChain.last().inverted = false;
1789 fragment.tagNameMatchedBacktrackingStartWidthFromIndirectAdjacent = computeBacktrackingStartOffsetInChain(tagNamesForDirectAdjacentChain, maxPrefixSize);
1790 fragment.widthFromIndirectAdjacent = tagNamesForDirectAdjacentChain.size() - 1;
1791 previousDirectAdjacentFragmentInDirectAdjacentChain = &fragment;
1792 }
1793}
1794
1795static bool requiresAdjacentTail(const SelectorFragment& fragment)
1796{
1797 ASSERT(fragment.traversalBacktrackingAction != BacktrackingAction::JumpToDirectAdjacentTail);
1798 return fragment.matchingTagNameBacktrackingAction == BacktrackingAction::JumpToDirectAdjacentTail || fragment.matchingPostTagNameBacktrackingAction == BacktrackingAction::JumpToDirectAdjacentTail;
1799}
1800
1801static bool requiresDescendantTail(const SelectorFragment& fragment)
1802{
1803 return fragment.matchingTagNameBacktrackingAction == BacktrackingAction::JumpToDescendantTail || fragment.matchingPostTagNameBacktrackingAction == BacktrackingAction::JumpToDescendantTail || fragment.traversalBacktrackingAction == BacktrackingAction::JumpToDescendantTail;
1804}
1805
1806void computeBacktrackingInformation(SelectorFragmentList& selectorFragments, unsigned level)
1807{
1808 bool hasDescendantRelationOnTheRight = false;
1809 unsigned ancestorPositionSinceDescendantRelation = 0;
1810 bool hasIndirectAdjacentRelationOnTheRightOfDirectAdjacentChain = false;
1811 unsigned adjacentPositionSinceIndirectAdjacentTreeWalk = 0;
1812
1813 bool needsAdjacentTail = false;
1814 bool needsDescendantTail = false;
1815 unsigned saveDescendantBacktrackingStartFragmentIndex = std::numeric_limits<unsigned>::max();
1816 unsigned saveIndirectAdjacentBacktrackingStartFragmentIndex = std::numeric_limits<unsigned>::max();
1817
1818 TagNameList tagNamesForChildChain;
1819 TagNameList tagNamesForDirectAdjacentChain;
1820 const SelectorFragment* previousChildFragmentInChildChain = nullptr;
1821 const SelectorFragment* previousDirectAdjacentFragmentInDirectAdjacentChain = nullptr;
1822
1823 for (unsigned i = 0; i < selectorFragments.size(); ++i) {
1824 SelectorFragment& fragment = selectorFragments[i];
1825
1826 updateChainStates(fragment, hasDescendantRelationOnTheRight, ancestorPositionSinceDescendantRelation, hasIndirectAdjacentRelationOnTheRightOfDirectAdjacentChain, adjacentPositionSinceIndirectAdjacentTreeWalk);
1827
1828 computeBacktrackingHeightFromDescendant(fragment, tagNamesForChildChain, hasDescendantRelationOnTheRight, previousChildFragmentInChildChain);
1829
1830 computeBacktrackingWidthFromIndirectAdjacent(fragment, tagNamesForDirectAdjacentChain, hasIndirectAdjacentRelationOnTheRightOfDirectAdjacentChain, previousDirectAdjacentFragmentInDirectAdjacentChain);
1831
1832#if CSS_SELECTOR_JIT_DEBUGGING
1833 dataLogF("%*sComputing fragment[%d] backtracking height %u. NotMatched %u / Matched %u | width %u. NotMatched %u / Matched %u\n", level * 4, "", i, fragment.heightFromDescendant, fragment.tagNameNotMatchedBacktrackingStartHeightFromDescendant, fragment.tagNameMatchedBacktrackingStartHeightFromDescendant, fragment.widthFromIndirectAdjacent, fragment.tagNameNotMatchedBacktrackingStartWidthFromIndirectAdjacent, fragment.tagNameMatchedBacktrackingStartWidthFromIndirectAdjacent);
1834#endif
1835
1836 solveBacktrackingAction(fragment, hasDescendantRelationOnTheRight, hasIndirectAdjacentRelationOnTheRightOfDirectAdjacentChain);
1837
1838 needsAdjacentTail |= requiresAdjacentTail(fragment);
1839 needsDescendantTail |= requiresDescendantTail(fragment);
1840
1841 // Add code generation flags.
1842 if (fragment.relationToLeftFragment != FragmentRelation::Descendant && fragment.relationToRightFragment == FragmentRelation::Descendant)
1843 fragment.backtrackingFlags |= BacktrackingFlag::DescendantEntryPoint;
1844 if (fragment.relationToLeftFragment == FragmentRelation::DirectAdjacent && fragment.relationToRightFragment == FragmentRelation::IndirectAdjacent)
1845 fragment.backtrackingFlags |= BacktrackingFlag::IndirectAdjacentEntryPoint;
1846 if (fragment.relationToLeftFragment != FragmentRelation::Descendant && fragment.relationToRightFragment == FragmentRelation::Child && isFirstAncestor(ancestorPositionSinceDescendantRelation)) {
1847 ASSERT(saveDescendantBacktrackingStartFragmentIndex == std::numeric_limits<unsigned>::max());
1848 saveDescendantBacktrackingStartFragmentIndex = i;
1849 }
1850 if (fragment.relationToLeftFragment == FragmentRelation::DirectAdjacent && fragment.relationToRightFragment == FragmentRelation::DirectAdjacent && isFirstAdjacent(adjacentPositionSinceIndirectAdjacentTreeWalk)) {
1851 ASSERT(saveIndirectAdjacentBacktrackingStartFragmentIndex == std::numeric_limits<unsigned>::max());
1852 saveIndirectAdjacentBacktrackingStartFragmentIndex = i;
1853 }
1854 if (fragment.relationToLeftFragment != FragmentRelation::DirectAdjacent) {
1855 if (needsAdjacentTail) {
1856 ASSERT(fragment.relationToRightFragment == FragmentRelation::DirectAdjacent);
1857 ASSERT(saveIndirectAdjacentBacktrackingStartFragmentIndex != std::numeric_limits<unsigned>::max());
1858 fragment.backtrackingFlags |= BacktrackingFlag::DirectAdjacentTail;
1859 selectorFragments[saveIndirectAdjacentBacktrackingStartFragmentIndex].backtrackingFlags |= BacktrackingFlag::SaveAdjacentBacktrackingStart;
1860 needsAdjacentTail = false;
1861 for (unsigned j = saveIndirectAdjacentBacktrackingStartFragmentIndex; j <= i; ++j)
1862 selectorFragments[j].backtrackingFlags |= BacktrackingFlag::InChainWithAdjacentTail;
1863 }
1864 saveIndirectAdjacentBacktrackingStartFragmentIndex = std::numeric_limits<unsigned>::max();
1865 }
1866 if (fragment.relationToLeftFragment == FragmentRelation::Descendant) {
1867 if (needsDescendantTail) {
1868 ASSERT(saveDescendantBacktrackingStartFragmentIndex != std::numeric_limits<unsigned>::max());
1869 fragment.backtrackingFlags |= BacktrackingFlag::DescendantTail;
1870 selectorFragments[saveDescendantBacktrackingStartFragmentIndex].backtrackingFlags |= BacktrackingFlag::SaveDescendantBacktrackingStart;
1871 needsDescendantTail = false;
1872 for (unsigned j = saveDescendantBacktrackingStartFragmentIndex; j <= i; ++j)
1873 selectorFragments[j].backtrackingFlags |= BacktrackingFlag::InChainWithDescendantTail;
1874 }
1875 saveDescendantBacktrackingStartFragmentIndex = std::numeric_limits<unsigned>::max();
1876 }
1877 }
1878
1879 for (SelectorFragment& fragment : selectorFragments) {
1880 if (!fragment.notFilters.isEmpty()) {
1881#if CSS_SELECTOR_JIT_DEBUGGING
1882 dataLogF("%*s Subselectors for :not():\n", level * 4, "");
1883#endif
1884
1885 for (SelectorFragmentList& selectorList : fragment.notFilters)
1886 computeBacktrackingInformation(selectorList, level + 1);
1887 }
1888
1889 if (!fragment.matchesFilters.isEmpty()) {
1890 for (SelectorList& matchesList : fragment.matchesFilters) {
1891#if CSS_SELECTOR_JIT_DEBUGGING
1892 dataLogF("%*s Subselectors for :matches():\n", level * 4, "");
1893#endif
1894
1895 for (SelectorFragmentList& selectorList : matchesList)
1896 computeBacktrackingInformation(selectorList, level + 1);
1897 }
1898 }
1899
1900 for (NthChildOfSelectorInfo& nthChildOfSelectorInfo : fragment.nthChildOfFilters) {
1901#if CSS_SELECTOR_JIT_DEBUGGING
1902 dataLogF("%*s Subselectors for %dn+%d:\n", level * 4, "", nthChildOfSelectorInfo.a, nthChildOfSelectorInfo.b);
1903#endif
1904
1905 for (SelectorFragmentList& selectorList : nthChildOfSelectorInfo.selectorList)
1906 computeBacktrackingInformation(selectorList, level + 1);
1907 }
1908
1909 for (NthChildOfSelectorInfo& nthLastChildOfSelectorInfo : fragment.nthLastChildOfFilters) {
1910#if CSS_SELECTOR_JIT_DEBUGGING
1911 dataLogF("%*s Subselectors for %dn+%d:\n", level * 4, "", nthLastChildOfSelectorInfo.a, nthLastChildOfSelectorInfo.b);
1912#endif
1913
1914 for (SelectorFragmentList& selectorList : nthLastChildOfSelectorInfo.selectorList)
1915 computeBacktrackingInformation(selectorList, level + 1);
1916 }
1917 }
1918}
1919
1920inline void SelectorCodeGenerator::pushMacroAssemblerRegisters()
1921{
1922#if CPU(ARM_THUMB2)
1923 // r6 is tempRegister in RegisterAllocator.h and addressTempRegister in MacroAssemblerARMv7.h and must be preserved by the callee.
1924 Vector<JSC::MacroAssembler::RegisterID, 1> macroAssemblerRegisters({ JSC::ARMRegisters::r6 });
1925 m_macroAssemblerRegistersStackReferences = m_stackAllocator.push(macroAssemblerRegisters);
1926#endif
1927}
1928
1929inline void SelectorCodeGenerator::popMacroAssemblerRegisters(StackAllocator& stackAllocator)
1930{
1931#if CPU(ARM_THUMB2)
1932 Vector<JSC::MacroAssembler::RegisterID, 1> macroAssemblerRegisters({ JSC::ARMRegisters::r6 });
1933 stackAllocator.pop(m_macroAssemblerRegistersStackReferences, macroAssemblerRegisters);
1934#else
1935 UNUSED_PARAM(stackAllocator);
1936#endif
1937}
1938
1939inline bool SelectorCodeGenerator::generatePrologue()
1940{
1941#if CPU(ARM64)
1942 Vector<JSC::MacroAssembler::RegisterID, 2> prologueRegisters;
1943 prologueRegisters.append(JSC::ARM64Registers::lr);
1944 prologueRegisters.append(JSC::ARM64Registers::fp);
1945 m_prologueStackReferences = m_stackAllocator.push(prologueRegisters);
1946 return true;
1947#elif CPU(ARM_THUMB2)
1948 Vector<JSC::MacroAssembler::RegisterID, 1> prologueRegisters;
1949 prologueRegisters.append(JSC::ARMRegisters::lr);
1950 m_prologueStackReferences = m_stackAllocator.push(prologueRegisters);
1951 return true;
1952#elif CPU(X86_64) && CSS_SELECTOR_JIT_DEBUGGING
1953 Vector<JSC::MacroAssembler::RegisterID, 1> prologueRegister;
1954 prologueRegister.append(callFrameRegister);
1955 m_prologueStackReferences = m_stackAllocator.push(prologueRegister);
1956 return true;
1957#endif
1958 return false;
1959}
1960
1961inline void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateEpilogue(StackAllocator& stackAllocator)
1962{
1963#if CPU(ARM64)
1964 Vector<JSC::MacroAssembler::RegisterID, 2> prologueRegisters({ JSC::ARM64Registers::lr, JSC::ARM64Registers::fp });
1965 stackAllocator.pop(m_prologueStackReferences, prologueRegisters);
1966#elif CPU(ARM_THUMB2)
1967 Vector<JSC::MacroAssembler::RegisterID, 1> prologueRegister({ JSC::ARMRegisters::lr });
1968 stackAllocator.pop(m_prologueStackReferences, prologueRegister);
1969#elif CPU(X86_64) && CSS_SELECTOR_JIT_DEBUGGING
1970 Vector<JSC::MacroAssembler::RegisterID, 1> prologueRegister({ callFrameRegister });
1971 stackAllocator.pop(m_prologueStackReferences, prologueRegister);
1972#else
1973 UNUSED_PARAM(stackAllocator);
1974#endif
1975}
1976
1977inline void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateReturn()
1978{
1979#if CPU(ARM64E)
1980 if (JSC::Options::useJITCage()) {
1981 m_assembler.farJump(Assembler::TrustedImmPtr(retagCodePtr<void*, CFunctionPtrTag, JSC::OperationPtrTag>(&vmEntryToCSSJITAfter)), JSC::OperationPtrTag);
1982 return;
1983 }
1984#endif
1985 m_assembler.ret();
1986}
1987
1988static bool isAdjacentRelation(FragmentRelation relation)
1989{
1990 return relation == FragmentRelation::DirectAdjacent || relation == FragmentRelation::IndirectAdjacent;
1991}
1992
1993static bool shouldMarkStyleIsAffectedByPreviousSibling(const SelectorFragment& fragment)
1994{
1995 return isAdjacentRelation(fragment.relationToLeftFragment) && !isAdjacentRelation(fragment.relationToRightFragment);
1996}
1997
1998void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateSelectorChecker()
1999{
2000 if (!JSC::Options::useJITCage())
2001 m_assembler.tagReturnAddress();
2002 pushMacroAssemblerRegisters();
2003 StackAllocator earlyFailureStack = m_stackAllocator;
2004
2005 Assembler::JumpList failureOnFunctionEntry;
2006 // Test selector's pseudo element equals to requested PseudoId.
2007 if (m_selectorContext != SelectorContext::QuerySelector && m_functionType == FunctionType::SelectorCheckerWithCheckingContext) {
2008 ASSERT_WITH_MESSAGE(fragmentMatchesTheRightmostElement(m_selectorFragments.first()), "Matching pseudo elements only make sense for the rightmost fragment.");
2009 generateRequestedPseudoElementEqualsToSelectorPseudoElement(failureOnFunctionEntry, m_selectorFragments.first(), checkingContextRegister);
2010 }
2011
2012 if (m_selectorContext == SelectorContext::RuleCollector) {
2013 unsigned specificity = m_selectorFragments.staticSpecificity;
2014 if (m_functionType == FunctionType::SelectorCheckerWithCheckingContext)
2015 m_assembler.store32(Assembler::TrustedImm32(specificity), JSC::GPRInfo::argumentGPR2);
2016 else
2017 m_assembler.store32(Assembler::TrustedImm32(specificity), JSC::GPRInfo::argumentGPR1);
2018 }
2019
2020 computeBacktrackingMemoryRequirements(m_selectorFragments);
2021 unsigned availableRegisterCount = m_registerAllocator.reserveCallerSavedRegisters(m_selectorFragments.registerRequirements);
2022
2023#if CSS_SELECTOR_JIT_DEBUGGING
2024 dataLogF("Compiling with minimum required register count %u, minimum stack space %u\n", m_selectorFragments.registerRequirements, m_selectorFragments.stackRequirements);
2025#endif
2026
2027 // We do not want unbounded stack allocation for backtracking. Going down 8 enry points would already be incredibly inefficient.
2028 unsigned maximumBacktrackingAllocations = 8;
2029 if (m_selectorFragments.stackRequirements > maximumBacktrackingAllocations) {
2030 m_assembler.move(Assembler::TrustedImm32(0), returnRegister);
2031 popMacroAssemblerRegisters(m_stackAllocator);
2032 generateReturn();
2033 return;
2034 }
2035
2036 bool needsEpilogue = generatePrologue();
2037
2038 StackAllocator::StackReferenceVector calleeSavedRegisterStackReferences;
2039 bool reservedCalleeSavedRegisters = false;
2040 ASSERT(m_selectorFragments.registerRequirements <= maximumRegisterCount);
2041 if (availableRegisterCount < m_selectorFragments.registerRequirements) {
2042 reservedCalleeSavedRegisters = true;
2043 calleeSavedRegisterStackReferences = m_stackAllocator.push(m_registerAllocator.reserveCalleeSavedRegisters(m_selectorFragments.registerRequirements - availableRegisterCount));
2044 }
2045
2046 m_registerAllocator.allocateRegister(elementAddressRegister);
2047
2048 StackAllocator::StackReference temporaryStackBase = m_stackAllocator.stackTop();
2049
2050 if (m_functionType == FunctionType::SelectorCheckerWithCheckingContext)
2051 m_checkingContextStackReference = m_stackAllocator.push(checkingContextRegister);
2052
2053 unsigned stackRequirementCount = m_selectorFragments.stackRequirements;
2054 if (m_visitedMode == VisitedMode::Visited)
2055 stackRequirementCount += 2;
2056
2057 StackAllocator::StackReferenceVector temporaryStack;
2058 if (stackRequirementCount)
2059 temporaryStack = m_stackAllocator.allocateUninitialized(stackRequirementCount);
2060
2061 if (m_visitedMode == VisitedMode::Visited) {
2062 m_lastVisitedElement = temporaryStack.takeLast();
2063 m_startElement = temporaryStack.takeLast();
2064 m_assembler.storePtr(elementAddressRegister, m_stackAllocator.addressOf(m_startElement));
2065 m_assembler.storePtr(Assembler::TrustedImmPtr(nullptr), m_stackAllocator.addressOf(m_lastVisitedElement));
2066 }
2067
2068 m_backtrackingStack = temporaryStack;
2069
2070 Assembler::JumpList failureCases;
2071 generateSelectorCheckerExcludingPseudoElements(failureCases, m_selectorFragments);
2072
2073 if (m_selectorContext != SelectorContext::QuerySelector && m_functionType == FunctionType::SelectorCheckerWithCheckingContext) {
2074 ASSERT(!m_selectorFragments.isEmpty());
2075 generateMarkPseudoStyleForPseudoElement(failureCases, m_selectorFragments.first());
2076 }
2077
2078 if (m_visitedMode == VisitedMode::Visited) {
2079 LocalRegister lastVisitedElement(m_registerAllocator);
2080 m_assembler.loadPtr(m_stackAllocator.addressOf(m_lastVisitedElement), lastVisitedElement);
2081 Assembler::Jump noLastVisitedElement = m_assembler.branchTestPtr(Assembler::Zero, lastVisitedElement);
2082 generateElementIsFirstLink(failureCases, lastVisitedElement);
2083 noLastVisitedElement.link(&m_assembler);
2084 }
2085
2086 m_registerAllocator.deallocateRegister(elementAddressRegister);
2087
2088 if (m_functionType == FunctionType::SimpleSelectorChecker) {
2089 if (temporaryStackBase == m_stackAllocator.stackTop() && !reservedCalleeSavedRegisters && !needsEpilogue) {
2090 StackAllocator successStack = m_stackAllocator;
2091 StackAllocator failureStack = m_stackAllocator;
2092
2093 ASSERT(!m_selectorFragments.stackRequirements);
2094 // Success.
2095 m_assembler.move(Assembler::TrustedImm32(1), returnRegister);
2096 popMacroAssemblerRegisters(successStack);
2097 generateReturn();
2098
2099 // Failure.
2100 ASSERT_WITH_MESSAGE(failureOnFunctionEntry.empty(), "Early failure on function entry is used for pseudo element. When early failure is used, function type is SelectorCheckerWithCheckingContext.");
2101 if (!failureCases.empty()) {
2102 failureCases.link(&m_assembler);
2103 m_assembler.move(Assembler::TrustedImm32(0), returnRegister);
2104 popMacroAssemblerRegisters(failureStack);
2105 generateReturn();
2106 } else
2107 failureStack = successStack;
2108
2109 m_stackAllocator.merge(WTFMove(successStack), WTFMove(failureStack));
2110 return;
2111 }
2112 }
2113
2114 // Success.
2115 m_assembler.move(Assembler::TrustedImm32(1), returnRegister);
2116
2117 // Failure.
2118 if (!failureCases.empty()) {
2119 Assembler::Jump skipFailureCase = m_assembler.jump();
2120 failureCases.link(&m_assembler);
2121 m_assembler.move(Assembler::TrustedImm32(0), returnRegister);
2122 skipFailureCase.link(&m_assembler);
2123 }
2124
2125 if (temporaryStackBase != m_stackAllocator.stackTop())
2126 m_stackAllocator.popAndDiscardUpTo(temporaryStackBase);
2127 if (reservedCalleeSavedRegisters)
2128 m_stackAllocator.pop(calleeSavedRegisterStackReferences, m_registerAllocator.restoreCalleeSavedRegisters());
2129
2130 StackAllocator successStack = m_stackAllocator;
2131 if (needsEpilogue)
2132 generateEpilogue(successStack);
2133 popMacroAssemblerRegisters(successStack);
2134 generateReturn();
2135
2136 // Early failure on function entry case.
2137 if (!failureOnFunctionEntry.empty()) {
2138 failureOnFunctionEntry.link(&m_assembler);
2139 m_assembler.move(Assembler::TrustedImm32(0), returnRegister);
2140 popMacroAssemblerRegisters(earlyFailureStack);
2141 generateReturn();
2142 } else
2143 earlyFailureStack = successStack;
2144 m_stackAllocator.merge(WTFMove(successStack), WTFMove(earlyFailureStack));
2145}
2146
2147void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateSelectorCheckerExcludingPseudoElements(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases, const SelectorFragmentList& selectorFragmentList)
2148{
2149 m_backtrackingLevels.append(BacktrackingLevel());
2150
2151 for (const SelectorFragment& fragment : selectorFragmentList) {
2152 switch (fragment.relationToRightFragment) {
2153 case FragmentRelation::Rightmost:
2154 generateRightmostTreeWalker(failureCases, fragment);
2155 break;
2156 case FragmentRelation::Descendant:
2157 generateAncestorTreeWalker(failureCases, fragment);
2158 break;
2159 case FragmentRelation::Child:
2160 generateParentElementTreeWalker(failureCases, fragment);
2161 break;
2162 case FragmentRelation::DirectAdjacent:
2163 generateDirectAdjacentTreeWalker(failureCases, fragment);
2164 break;
2165 case FragmentRelation::IndirectAdjacent:
2166 generateIndirectAdjacentTreeWalker(failureCases, fragment);
2167 break;
2168 }
2169 if (shouldMarkStyleIsAffectedByPreviousSibling(fragment)) {
2170 if (fragmentMatchesTheRightmostElement(fragment))
2171 generateAddStyleRelationIfResolvingStyle(elementAddressRegister, Style::Relation::AffectedByPreviousSibling);
2172 else
2173 generateAddStyleRelationIfResolvingStyle(elementAddressRegister, Style::Relation::DescendantsAffectedByPreviousSibling);
2174 }
2175 generateBacktrackingTailsIfNeeded(failureCases, fragment);
2176 }
2177
2178 ASSERT(!m_backtrackingLevels.last().descendantBacktrackingStart.isValid());
2179 ASSERT(!m_backtrackingLevels.last().adjacentBacktrackingStart.isValid());
2180 m_backtrackingLevels.takeLast();
2181}
2182
2183void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateElementMatchesSelectorList(Assembler::JumpList& failingCases, Assembler::RegisterID elementToMatch, const SelectorList& selectorList)
2184{
2185 ASSERT(!selectorList.isEmpty());
2186
2187 RegisterVector registersToSave;
2188
2189 // The contract is that existing registers are preserved. Two special cases are elementToMatch and elementAddressRegister
2190 // because they are used by the matcher itself.
2191 // To simplify things for now, we just always preserve them on the stack.
2192 unsigned elementToTestIndex = std::numeric_limits<unsigned>::max();
2193 bool isElementToMatchOnStack = false;
2194 if (selectorList.clobberElementAddressRegister) {
2195 if (elementToMatch != elementAddressRegister) {
2196 registersToSave.append(elementAddressRegister);
2197 registersToSave.append(elementToMatch);
2198 elementToTestIndex = 1;
2199 isElementToMatchOnStack = true;
2200 } else {
2201 registersToSave.append(elementAddressRegister);
2202 elementToTestIndex = 0;
2203 }
2204 } else if (elementToMatch != elementAddressRegister)
2205 registersToSave.append(elementAddressRegister);
2206
2207 // Next, we need to free as many registers as needed by the nested selector list.
2208 unsigned availableRegisterCount = m_registerAllocator.availableRegisterCount();
2209
2210 // Do not count elementAddressRegister, it will remain allocated.
2211 ++availableRegisterCount;
2212
2213 if (isElementToMatchOnStack)
2214 ++availableRegisterCount;
2215
2216 if (selectorList.registerRequirements > availableRegisterCount) {
2217 unsigned registerToPushCount = selectorList.registerRequirements - availableRegisterCount;
2218 for (Assembler::RegisterID registerId : m_registerAllocator.allocatedRegisters()) {
2219 if (registerId == elementAddressRegister)
2220 continue; // Handled separately above.
2221 if (isElementToMatchOnStack && registerId == elementToMatch)
2222 continue; // Do not push the element twice to the stack!
2223
2224 registersToSave.append(registerId);
2225
2226 --registerToPushCount;
2227 if (!registerToPushCount)
2228 break;
2229 }
2230 }
2231
2232 StackAllocator::StackReferenceVector allocatedRegistersOnStack = m_stackAllocator.push(registersToSave);
2233 for (Assembler::RegisterID registerID : registersToSave) {
2234 if (registerID != elementAddressRegister)
2235 m_registerAllocator.deallocateRegister(registerID);
2236 }
2237
2238
2239 if (elementToMatch != elementAddressRegister)
2240 m_assembler.move(elementToMatch, elementAddressRegister);
2241
2242 Assembler::JumpList localFailureCases;
2243 if (selectorList.size() == 1) {
2244 const SelectorFragmentList& nestedSelectorFragmentList = selectorList.first();
2245 generateSelectorCheckerExcludingPseudoElements(localFailureCases, nestedSelectorFragmentList);
2246 } else {
2247 Assembler::JumpList matchFragmentList;
2248
2249 unsigned selectorListSize = selectorList.size();
2250 unsigned selectorListLastIndex = selectorListSize - 1;
2251 for (unsigned i = 0; i < selectorList.size(); ++i) {
2252 const SelectorFragmentList& nestedSelectorFragmentList = selectorList[i];
2253 Assembler::JumpList localSelectorFailureCases;
2254 generateSelectorCheckerExcludingPseudoElements(localSelectorFailureCases, nestedSelectorFragmentList);
2255 if (i != selectorListLastIndex) {
2256 matchFragmentList.append(m_assembler.jump());
2257 localSelectorFailureCases.link(&m_assembler);
2258
2259 if (nestedSelectorFragmentList.clobberElementAddressRegister) {
2260 RELEASE_ASSERT(elementToTestIndex != std::numeric_limits<unsigned>::max());
2261 m_assembler.loadPtr(m_stackAllocator.addressOf(allocatedRegistersOnStack[elementToTestIndex]), elementAddressRegister);
2262 }
2263 } else
2264 localFailureCases.append(localSelectorFailureCases);
2265 }
2266 matchFragmentList.link(&m_assembler);
2267 }
2268
2269 // Finally, restore all the registers in the state they were before this selector checker.
2270 for (Assembler::RegisterID registerID : registersToSave) {
2271 if (registerID != elementAddressRegister)
2272 m_registerAllocator.allocateRegister(registerID);
2273 }
2274
2275 if (allocatedRegistersOnStack.isEmpty()) {
2276 failingCases.append(localFailureCases);
2277 return;
2278 }
2279
2280 if (localFailureCases.empty())
2281 m_stackAllocator.pop(allocatedRegistersOnStack, registersToSave);
2282 else {
2283 StackAllocator successStack = m_stackAllocator;
2284 StackAllocator failureStack = m_stackAllocator;
2285
2286 successStack.pop(allocatedRegistersOnStack, registersToSave);
2287
2288 Assembler::Jump skipFailureCase = m_assembler.jump();
2289 localFailureCases.link(&m_assembler);
2290 failureStack.pop(allocatedRegistersOnStack, registersToSave);
2291 failingCases.append(m_assembler.jump());
2292
2293 skipFailureCase.link(&m_assembler);
2294
2295 m_stackAllocator.merge(WTFMove(successStack), WTFMove(failureStack));
2296 }
2297}
2298
2299void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateRightmostTreeWalker(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases, const SelectorFragment& fragment)
2300{
2301 generateElementMatching(failureCases, failureCases, fragment);
2302}

2305{
2306 m_assembler.loadPtr(Assembler::Address(elementAddressRegister, Node::parentNodeMemoryOffset()), targetRegister);
2307}

2309void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateWalkToParentElement(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases, Assembler::RegisterID targetRegister)
2310{
2311 // ContainerNode* parent = parentNode()
2312 // if (!parent || !parent->isElementNode())
2313 // failure
2314 generateWalkToParentNode(targetRegister);
2315 failureCases.append(m_assembler.branchTestPtr(Assembler::Zero, targetRegister));
2316 failureCases.append(DOMJIT::branchTestIsElementFlagOnNode(m_assembler, Assembler::Zero, targetRegister));
2317}

2319void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateWalkToParentElementOrShadowRoot(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases, Assembler::RegisterID targetRegister)
2320{
2321 // ContainerNode* parent = parentNode()
2322 // if (!parent || !(parent->isElementNode() || parent->isShadowRoot()))
2323 // failure
2324 generateWalkToParentNode(targetRegister);
2325 failureCases.append(m_assembler.branchTestPtr(Assembler::Zero, targetRegister));
2326 failureCases.append(DOMJIT::branchTestIsElementOrShadowRootFlagOnNode(m_assembler, Assembler::Zero, targetRegister));
2327}
