2329void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateParentElementTreeWalker(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases, const SelectorFragment& fragment)
2330{
2331 Assembler::JumpList traversalFailureCases;
2332 generateWalkToParentElement(traversalFailureCases, elementAddressRegister);
2333 linkFailures(failureCases, fragment.traversalBacktrackingAction, traversalFailureCases);
2334
2335 Assembler::JumpList matchingTagNameFailureCases;
2336 Assembler::JumpList matchingPostTagNameFailureCases;
2337 generateElementMatching(matchingTagNameFailureCases, matchingPostTagNameFailureCases, fragment);
2338 linkFailures(failureCases, fragment.matchingTagNameBacktrackingAction, matchingTagNameFailureCases);
2339 linkFailures(failureCases, fragment.matchingPostTagNameBacktrackingAction, matchingPostTagNameFailureCases);
2340
2341 if (fragment.backtrackingFlags & BacktrackingFlag::SaveDescendantBacktrackingStart) {
2342 if (!m_descendantBacktrackingStartInUse) {
2343 m_descendantBacktrackingStart = m_registerAllocator.allocateRegister();
2344 m_assembler.move(elementAddressRegister, m_descendantBacktrackingStart);
2345 m_descendantBacktrackingStartInUse = true;
2346 } else {
2347 BacktrackingLevel& currentBacktrackingLevel = m_backtrackingLevels.last();
2348 ASSERT(!currentBacktrackingLevel.descendantBacktrackingStart.isValid());
2349 currentBacktrackingLevel.descendantBacktrackingStart = m_backtrackingStack.takeLast();
2350
2351 m_assembler.storePtr(elementAddressRegister, m_stackAllocator.addressOf(currentBacktrackingLevel.descendantBacktrackingStart));
2352 }
2353 }
2354}
2355
2356void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateAncestorTreeWalker(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases, const SelectorFragment& fragment)
2357{
2358 // Loop over the ancestors until one of them matches the fragment.
2359 Assembler::Label loopStart(m_assembler.label());
2360
2361 if (fragment.backtrackingFlags & BacktrackingFlag::DescendantEntryPoint)
2362 m_backtrackingLevels.last().descendantTreeWalkerBacktrackingPoint = m_assembler.label();
2363
2364 generateWalkToParentElement(failureCases, elementAddressRegister);
2365
2366 if (fragment.backtrackingFlags & BacktrackingFlag::DescendantEntryPoint)
2367 m_backtrackingLevels.last().descendantEntryPoint = m_assembler.label();
2368
2369 Assembler::JumpList matchingFailureCases;
2370 generateElementMatching(matchingFailureCases, matchingFailureCases, fragment);
2371 matchingFailureCases.linkTo(loopStart, &m_assembler);
2372}

2374inline void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateWalkToNextAdjacentElement(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases, Assembler::RegisterID workRegister)
2375{
2376 Assembler::Label loopStart = m_assembler.label();
2377 m_assembler.loadPtr(Assembler::Address(workRegister, Node::nextSiblingMemoryOffset()), workRegister);
2378 failureCases.append(m_assembler.branchTestPtr(Assembler::Zero, workRegister));
2379 DOMJIT::branchTestIsElementFlagOnNode(m_assembler, Assembler::Zero, workRegister).linkTo(loopStart, &m_assembler);
2380}
2381
2382inline void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateWalkToPreviousAdjacentElement(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases, Assembler::RegisterID workRegister)
2383{
2384 Assembler::Label loopStart = m_assembler.label();
2385 m_assembler.loadPtr(Assembler::Address(workRegister, Node::previousSiblingMemoryOffset()), workRegister);
2386 failureCases.append(m_assembler.branchTestPtr(Assembler::Zero, workRegister));
2387 DOMJIT::branchTestIsElementFlagOnNode(m_assembler, Assembler::Zero, workRegister).linkTo(loopStart, &m_assembler);
2388}
2389
2390void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateWalkToPreviousAdjacent(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases, const SelectorFragment& fragment)
2391{
2392 // do {
2393 // previousSibling = previousSibling->previousSibling();
2394 // if (!previousSibling)
2395 // failure!
2396 // while (!previousSibling->isElement());
2397 Assembler::RegisterID previousSibling;
2398 bool useTailOnTraversalFailure = fragment.traversalBacktrackingAction >= BacktrackingAction::JumpToDescendantTail;
2399 if (!useTailOnTraversalFailure) {
2400 // If the current fragment is not dependant on a previously saved elementAddressRegister, a fast recover
2401 // from a failure would resume with elementAddressRegister.
2402 // When walking to the previous sibling, the failure can be that previousSibling is null. We cannot backtrack
2403 // with a null elementAddressRegister so we do the traversal on a copy.
2404 previousSibling = m_registerAllocator.allocateRegister();
2405 m_assembler.move(elementAddressRegister, previousSibling);
2406 } else
2407 previousSibling = elementAddressRegister;
2408
2409 Assembler::JumpList traversalFailureCases;
2410 generateWalkToPreviousAdjacentElement(traversalFailureCases, previousSibling);
2411 linkFailures(failureCases, fragment.traversalBacktrackingAction, traversalFailureCases);
2412
2413 // On success, move previousSibling over to elementAddressRegister if we could not work on elementAddressRegister directly.
2414 if (!useTailOnTraversalFailure) {
2415 m_assembler.move(previousSibling, elementAddressRegister);
2416 m_registerAllocator.deallocateRegister(previousSibling);
2417 }
2418}
2419
2420void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateDirectAdjacentTreeWalker(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases, const SelectorFragment& fragment)
2421{
2422 generateWalkToPreviousAdjacent(failureCases, fragment);
2423 generateAddStyleRelationIfResolvingStyle(elementAddressRegister, Style::Relation::AffectsNextSibling);
2424
2425 Assembler::JumpList matchingTagNameFailureCases;
2426 Assembler::JumpList matchingPostTagNameFailureCases;
2427 generateElementMatching(matchingTagNameFailureCases, matchingPostTagNameFailureCases, fragment);
2428 linkFailures(failureCases, fragment.matchingTagNameBacktrackingAction, matchingTagNameFailureCases);
2429 linkFailures(failureCases, fragment.matchingPostTagNameBacktrackingAction, matchingPostTagNameFailureCases);
2430
2431 if (fragment.backtrackingFlags & BacktrackingFlag::SaveAdjacentBacktrackingStart) {
2432 BacktrackingLevel& currentBacktrackingLevel = m_backtrackingLevels.last();
2433 ASSERT(!currentBacktrackingLevel.adjacentBacktrackingStart.isValid());
2434 currentBacktrackingLevel.adjacentBacktrackingStart = m_backtrackingStack.takeLast();
2435
2436 m_assembler.storePtr(elementAddressRegister, m_stackAllocator.addressOf(currentBacktrackingLevel.adjacentBacktrackingStart));
2437 }
2438}
2439
2440void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateIndirectAdjacentTreeWalker(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases, const SelectorFragment& fragment)
2441{
2442 Assembler::Label loopStart(m_assembler.label());
2443
2444 if (fragment.backtrackingFlags & BacktrackingFlag::IndirectAdjacentEntryPoint)
2445 m_backtrackingLevels.last().indirectAdjacentTreeWalkerBacktrackingPoint = m_assembler.label();
2446
2447 generateWalkToPreviousAdjacent(failureCases, fragment);
2448 generateAddStyleRelationIfResolvingStyle(elementAddressRegister, Style::Relation::AffectsNextSibling);
2449
2450 if (fragment.backtrackingFlags & BacktrackingFlag::IndirectAdjacentEntryPoint)
2451 m_backtrackingLevels.last().indirectAdjacentEntryPoint = m_assembler.label();
2452
2453 Assembler::JumpList localFailureCases;
2454 generateElementMatching(localFailureCases, localFailureCases, fragment);
2455 localFailureCases.linkTo(loopStart, &m_assembler);
2456}

2458void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateAddStyleRelationIfResolvingStyle(Assembler::RegisterID element, Style::Relation::Type relationType, std::optional<Assembler::RegisterID> value)
2459{
2460 if (m_selectorContext == SelectorContext::QuerySelector)
2461 return;
2462
2463 LocalRegister checkingContext(m_registerAllocator);
2464 Assembler::Jump notResolvingStyle = jumpIfNotResolvingStyle(checkingContext);
2465
2466 generateAddStyleRelation(checkingContext, element, relationType, value);
2467
2468 notResolvingStyle.link(&m_assembler);
2469}
2470
2471JSC_DEFINE_JIT_OPERATION(operationAddStyleRelationFunction, void, (SelectorChecker::CheckingContext* checkingContext, const Element* element))
2472{
2473 checkingContext->styleRelations.append({ *element, { }, 1 });
2474}
2475
2476#if CPU(ARM_THUMB2) && !CPU(APPLE_ARMV7S)
2477// FIXME: This could be implemented in assembly to avoid a function call, and we know the divisor at jit-compile time.
2478JSC_DEFINE_JIT_OPERATION(operationModuloHelper, int, (int dividend, int divisor))
2479{
2480 return dividend % divisor;
2481}
2482#endif
2483
2484void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateAddStyleRelation(Assembler::RegisterID checkingContext, Assembler::RegisterID element, Style::Relation::Type relationType, std::optional<Assembler::RegisterID> value)
2485{
2486 ASSERT(m_selectorContext != SelectorContext::QuerySelector);
2487
2488 Assembler::Address vectorAddress(checkingContext, OBJECT_OFFSETOF(SelectorChecker::CheckingContext, styleRelations));
2489 auto dataAddress = vectorAddress.withOffset(Style::Relations::dataMemoryOffset());
2490 auto sizeAddress = vectorAddress.withOffset(Style::Relations::sizeMemoryOffset());
2491
2492 auto getLastRelationPointer = [&] (Assembler::RegisterID sizeAndTarget) {
2493 m_assembler.sub32(Assembler::TrustedImm32(1), sizeAndTarget);
2494#if CPU(ADDRESS64)
2495 static_assert(sizeof(Style::Relation) == 16, "");
2496 static_assert(1 << 4 == 16, "");
2497 m_assembler.lshiftPtr(Assembler::TrustedImm32(4), sizeAndTarget);
2498#else
2499 m_assembler.mul32(Assembler::TrustedImm32(sizeof(Style::Relation)), sizeAndTarget, sizeAndTarget);
2500#endif
2501 m_assembler.addPtr(dataAddress, sizeAndTarget);
2502 };
2503
2504 // For AffectsNextSibling we just increment the count if the previous added relation was in the same sibling chain.
2505 Assembler::JumpList mergeSuccess;
2506 if (relationType == Style::Relation::AffectsNextSibling) {
2507 Assembler::JumpList mergeFailure;
2508
2509 LocalRegister lastRelation(m_registerAllocator);
2510 m_assembler.load32(sizeAddress, lastRelation);
2511
2512 // if (!checkingContext.styleRelations.isEmpty())
2513 mergeFailure.append(m_assembler.branchTest32(Assembler::Zero, lastRelation));
2514
2515 // Style::Relation& lastRelation = checkingContext.styleRelations.last();
2516 getLastRelationPointer(lastRelation);
2517
2518 // if (lastRelation.type == Style::Relation::AffectsNextSibling)
2519 Assembler::Address typeAddress(lastRelation, OBJECT_OFFSETOF(Style::Relation, type));
2520 mergeFailure.append(m_assembler.branch32(Assembler::NotEqual, typeAddress, Assembler::TrustedImm32(Style::Relation::AffectsNextSibling)));
2521
2522 Assembler::Address elementAddress(lastRelation, OBJECT_OFFSETOF(Style::Relation, element));
2523 {
2524 // if (element.nextSiblingElement() == lastRelation.element)
2525 LocalRegister nextSiblingElement(m_registerAllocator);
2526 m_assembler.move(element, nextSiblingElement);
2527 generateWalkToNextAdjacentElement(mergeFailure, nextSiblingElement);
2528 mergeFailure.append(m_assembler.branchPtr(Assembler::NotEqual, nextSiblingElement, elementAddress));
2529 }
2530
2531 // ++lastRelation.value;
2532 Assembler::Address valueAddress(lastRelation, OBJECT_OFFSETOF(Style::Relation, value));
2533 m_assembler.add32(Assembler::TrustedImm32(1), valueAddress);
2534
2535 // lastRelation.element = &element;
2536 m_assembler.storePtr(element, elementAddress);
2537
2538 mergeSuccess.append(m_assembler.jump());
2539 mergeFailure.link(&m_assembler);
2540 }
2541
2542 // FIXME: Append to vector without a function call at least when there is sufficient capacity.
2543 FunctionCall functionCall(m_assembler, m_registerAllocator, m_stackAllocator, m_functionCalls);
2544 functionCall.setFunctionAddress(operationAddStyleRelationFunction);
2545 functionCall.setTwoArguments(checkingContext, element);
2546 functionCall.call();
2547
2548 LocalRegister relationPointer(m_registerAllocator);
2549 m_assembler.load32(sizeAddress, relationPointer);
2550 getLastRelationPointer(relationPointer);
2551
2552 Assembler::Address typeAddress(relationPointer, OBJECT_OFFSETOF(Style::Relation, type));
2553 m_assembler.store32(Assembler::TrustedImm32(relationType), typeAddress);
2554
2555 if (value) {
2556 Assembler::Address valueAddress(relationPointer, OBJECT_OFFSETOF(Style::Relation, value));
2557 m_assembler.store32(*value, valueAddress);
2558 }
2559
2560 mergeSuccess.link(&m_assembler);
2561}

2563Assembler::JumpList SelectorCodeGenerator::jumpIfNoPreviousAdjacentElement()
2564{
2565 Assembler::JumpList successCase;
2566 LocalRegister previousSibling(m_registerAllocator);
2567 m_assembler.move(elementAddressRegister, previousSibling);
2568 generateWalkToPreviousAdjacentElement(successCase, previousSibling);
2569 return successCase;

2572Assembler::JumpList SelectorCodeGenerator::jumpIfNoNextAdjacentElement()
2573{
2574 Assembler::JumpList successCase;

2576 m_assembler.move(elementAddressRegister, nextSibling);

2589Assembler::Jump SelectorCodeGenerator::branchOnResolvingModeWithCheckingContext(Assembler::RelationalCondition condition, SelectorChecker::Mode mode, Assembler::RegisterID checkingContext)

2594
2595}

2608void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateSpecialFailureInQuirksModeForActiveAndHoverIfNeeded(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases, const SelectorFragment& fragment)
2609{
2610 if (fragment.onlyMatchesLinksInQuirksMode) {
2611 // If the element is a link, it can always match :hover or :active.
2612 Assembler::Jump isLink = m_assembler.branchTest32(Assembler::NonZero, Assembler::Address(elementAddressRegister, Node::nodeFlagsMemoryOffset()), Assembler::TrustedImm32(Node::flagIsLink()));
2613
2614 // Only quirks mode restrict :hover and :active.
2615 static_assert(sizeof(DocumentCompatibilityMode) == 1, "We generate a byte load/test for the compatibility mode.");
2616 LocalRegister documentAddress(m_registerAllocator);
2617 DOMJIT::loadDocument(m_assembler, elementAddressRegister, documentAddress);
2618 failureCases.append(m_assembler.branchTest8(Assembler::NonZero, Assembler::Address(documentAddress, Document::compatibilityModeMemoryOffset()), Assembler::TrustedImm32(static_cast<std::underlying_type<DocumentCompatibilityMode>::type>(DocumentCompatibilityMode::QuirksMode))));
2619
2620 isLink.link(&m_assembler);
2621 }
2622}
2623
2624// The value in inputDividend is destroyed by the modulo operation.
2625Assembler::Jump SelectorCodeGenerator::modulo(Assembler::ResultCondition condition, Assembler::RegisterID inputDividend, int divisor)
2626{
2627 RELEASE_ASSERT(divisor);
2628#if CPU(ARM64) || CPU(APPLE_ARMV7S)
2629 LocalRegister divisorRegister(m_registerAllocator);
2630 m_assembler.move(Assembler::TrustedImm32(divisor), divisorRegister);
2631
2632 LocalRegister resultRegister(m_registerAllocator);
2633 m_assembler.m_assembler.sdiv<32>(resultRegister, inputDividend, divisorRegister);
2634 m_assembler.mul32(divisorRegister, resultRegister);
2635 return m_assembler.branchSub32(condition, inputDividend, resultRegister, resultRegister);
2636#elif CPU(ARM_THUMB2) && !CPU(APPLE_ARMV7S)
2637 LocalRegisterWithPreference divisorRegister(m_registerAllocator, JSC::GPRInfo::argumentGPR1);
2638 m_assembler.move(Assembler::TrustedImm32(divisor), divisorRegister);
2639 FunctionCall functionCall(m_assembler, m_registerAllocator, m_stackAllocator, m_functionCalls);
2640 functionCall.setFunctionAddress(operationModuloHelper);
2641 functionCall.setTwoArguments(inputDividend, divisorRegister);
2642 return functionCall.callAndBranchOnBooleanReturnValue(condition);
2643#elif CPU(X86_64)
2644 // idiv takes RAX + an arbitrary register, and return RAX + RDX. Most of this code is about doing
2645 // an efficient allocation of those registers. If a register is already in use and is not the inputDividend,
2646 // we first try to copy it to a temporary register, it that is not possible we fall back to the stack.
2647 enum class RegisterAllocationType {
2648 External,
2649 AllocatedLocally,
2650 CopiedToTemporary,
2651 PushedToStack
2652 };
2653
2654 // 1) Get RAX and RDX.
2655 // If they are already used, push them to the stack.
2656 Assembler::RegisterID dividend = JSC::X86Registers::eax;
2657 RegisterAllocationType dividendAllocation = RegisterAllocationType::External;
2658 StackAllocator::StackReference temporaryDividendStackReference;
2659 Assembler::RegisterID temporaryDividendCopy = JSC::InvalidGPRReg;
2660 if (inputDividend != dividend) {
2661 bool registerIsInUse = m_registerAllocator.allocatedRegisters().contains(dividend);
2662 if (registerIsInUse) {
2663 if (m_registerAllocator.availableRegisterCount() > 1) {
2664 temporaryDividendCopy = m_registerAllocator.allocateRegister();
2665 m_assembler.move(dividend, temporaryDividendCopy);
2666 dividendAllocation = RegisterAllocationType::CopiedToTemporary;
2667 } else {
2668 temporaryDividendStackReference = m_stackAllocator.push(dividend);
2669 dividendAllocation = RegisterAllocationType::PushedToStack;
2670 }
2671 } else {
2672 m_registerAllocator.allocateRegister(dividend);
2673 dividendAllocation = RegisterAllocationType::AllocatedLocally;
2674 }
2675 m_assembler.move(inputDividend, dividend);
2676 }
2677
2678 Assembler::RegisterID remainder = JSC::X86Registers::edx;
2679 RegisterAllocationType remainderAllocation = RegisterAllocationType::External;
2680 StackAllocator::StackReference temporaryRemainderStackReference;
2681 Assembler::RegisterID temporaryRemainderCopy = JSC::InvalidGPRReg;
2682 if (inputDividend != remainder) {
2683 bool registerIsInUse = m_registerAllocator.allocatedRegisters().contains(remainder);
2684 if (registerIsInUse) {
2685 if (m_registerAllocator.availableRegisterCount() > 1) {
2686 temporaryRemainderCopy = m_registerAllocator.allocateRegister();
2687 m_assembler.move(remainder, temporaryRemainderCopy);
2688 remainderAllocation = RegisterAllocationType::CopiedToTemporary;
2689 } else {
2690 temporaryRemainderStackReference = m_stackAllocator.push(remainder);
2691 remainderAllocation = RegisterAllocationType::PushedToStack;
2692 }
2693 } else {
2694 m_registerAllocator.allocateRegister(remainder);
2695 remainderAllocation = RegisterAllocationType::AllocatedLocally;
2696 }
2697 }
2698
2699 // If the input register is used by idiv, save its value to restore it after the operation.
2700 Assembler::RegisterID inputDividendCopy = JSC::InvalidGPRReg;
2701 StackAllocator::StackReference pushedInputDividendStackReference;
2702 RegisterAllocationType savedInputDividendAllocationType = RegisterAllocationType::External;
2703 if (inputDividend == dividend || inputDividend == remainder) {
2704 if (m_registerAllocator.availableRegisterCount() > 1) {
2705 inputDividendCopy = m_registerAllocator.allocateRegister();
2706 m_assembler.move(inputDividend, inputDividendCopy);
2707 savedInputDividendAllocationType = RegisterAllocationType::CopiedToTemporary;
2708 } else {
2709 pushedInputDividendStackReference = m_stackAllocator.push(inputDividend);
2710 savedInputDividendAllocationType = RegisterAllocationType::PushedToStack;
2711 }
2712 }
2713
2714 m_assembler.m_assembler.cdq();
2715
2716 // 2) Perform the division with idiv.
2717 {
2718 LocalRegister divisorRegister(m_registerAllocator);
2719 m_assembler.move(Assembler::TrustedImm64(divisor), divisorRegister);
2720 m_assembler.m_assembler.idivl_r(divisorRegister);
2721 m_assembler.test32(remainder);
2722 }
2723
2724 // 3) Return RAX and RDX.
2725 if (remainderAllocation == RegisterAllocationType::AllocatedLocally)
2726 m_registerAllocator.deallocateRegister(remainder);
2727 else if (remainderAllocation == RegisterAllocationType::CopiedToTemporary) {
2728 m_assembler.move(temporaryRemainderCopy, remainder);
2729 m_registerAllocator.deallocateRegister(temporaryRemainderCopy);
2730 } else if (remainderAllocation == RegisterAllocationType::PushedToStack)
2731 m_stackAllocator.pop(temporaryRemainderStackReference, remainder);
2732
2733 if (dividendAllocation == RegisterAllocationType::AllocatedLocally)
2734 m_registerAllocator.deallocateRegister(dividend);
2735 else if (dividendAllocation == RegisterAllocationType::CopiedToTemporary) {
2736 m_assembler.move(temporaryDividendCopy, dividend);
2737 m_registerAllocator.deallocateRegister(temporaryDividendCopy);
2738 } else if (dividendAllocation == RegisterAllocationType::PushedToStack)
2739 m_stackAllocator.pop(temporaryDividendStackReference, dividend);
2740
2741 if (savedInputDividendAllocationType != RegisterAllocationType::External) {
2742 if (savedInputDividendAllocationType == RegisterAllocationType::CopiedToTemporary) {
2743 m_assembler.move(inputDividendCopy, inputDividend);
2744 m_registerAllocator.deallocateRegister(inputDividendCopy);
2745 } else if (savedInputDividendAllocationType == RegisterAllocationType::PushedToStack)
2746 m_stackAllocator.pop(pushedInputDividendStackReference, inputDividend);
2747 }
2748
2749 // 4) Branch on the test.
2750 return m_assembler.branch(condition);
2751#else
2752#error Modulo is not implemented for this architecture.
2753#endif
2754}
2755
2756void SelectorCodeGenerator::moduloIsZero(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases, Assembler::RegisterID inputDividend, int divisor)
2757{
2758 if (divisor == 1 || divisor == -1)
2759 return;
2760 if (divisor == 2 || divisor == -2) {
2761 failureCases.append(m_assembler.branchTest32(Assembler::NonZero, inputDividend, Assembler::TrustedImm32(1)));
2762 return;
2763 }
2764
2765 failureCases.append(modulo(Assembler::NonZero, inputDividend, divisor));
2766}
2767
2768void SelectorCodeGenerator::linkFailures(Assembler::JumpList& globalFailureCases, BacktrackingAction backtrackingAction, Assembler::JumpList& localFailureCases)
2769{
2770 switch (backtrackingAction) {
2771 case BacktrackingAction::NoBacktracking:
2772 globalFailureCases.append(localFailureCases);
2773 break;
2774 case BacktrackingAction::JumpToDescendantEntryPoint:
2775 localFailureCases.linkTo(m_backtrackingLevels.last().descendantEntryPoint, &m_assembler);
2776 break;
2777 case BacktrackingAction::JumpToDescendantTreeWalkerEntryPoint:
2778 localFailureCases.linkTo(m_backtrackingLevels.last().descendantTreeWalkerBacktrackingPoint, &m_assembler);
2779 break;
2780 case BacktrackingAction::JumpToDescendantTail:
2781 m_backtrackingLevels.last().descendantBacktrackingFailureCases.append(localFailureCases);
2782 break;
2783 case BacktrackingAction::JumpToIndirectAdjacentEntryPoint:
2784 localFailureCases.linkTo(m_backtrackingLevels.last().indirectAdjacentEntryPoint, &m_assembler);
2785 break;
2786 case BacktrackingAction::JumpToIndirectAdjacentTreeWalkerEntryPoint:
2787 localFailureCases.linkTo(m_backtrackingLevels.last().indirectAdjacentTreeWalkerBacktrackingPoint, &m_assembler);
2788 break;
2789 case BacktrackingAction::JumpToDirectAdjacentTail:
2790 m_backtrackingLevels.last().adjacentBacktrackingFailureCases.append(localFailureCases);
2791 break;
2792 }
2793}
2794
2795void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateAdjacentBacktrackingTail()
2796{
2797 // Recovering tail.
2798 m_backtrackingLevels.last().adjacentBacktrackingFailureCases.link(&m_assembler);
2799 m_backtrackingLevels.last().adjacentBacktrackingFailureCases.clear();
2800
2801 BacktrackingLevel& currentBacktrackingLevel = m_backtrackingLevels.last();
2802 m_assembler.loadPtr(m_stackAllocator.addressOf(currentBacktrackingLevel.adjacentBacktrackingStart), elementAddressRegister);
2803 m_backtrackingStack.append(currentBacktrackingLevel.adjacentBacktrackingStart);
2804 currentBacktrackingLevel.adjacentBacktrackingStart = StackAllocator::StackReference();
2805
2806 m_assembler.jump(m_backtrackingLevels.last().indirectAdjacentEntryPoint);
2807}
2808
2809void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateDescendantBacktrackingTail()
2810{
2811 m_backtrackingLevels.last().descendantBacktrackingFailureCases.link(&m_assembler);
2812 m_backtrackingLevels.last().descendantBacktrackingFailureCases.clear();
2813
2814 BacktrackingLevel& currentBacktrackingLevel = m_backtrackingLevels.last();
2815 if (!currentBacktrackingLevel.descendantBacktrackingStart.isValid()) {
2816 m_assembler.move(m_descendantBacktrackingStart, elementAddressRegister);
2817 m_registerAllocator.deallocateRegister(m_descendantBacktrackingStart);
2818 m_descendantBacktrackingStartInUse = false;
2819 } else {
2820 m_assembler.loadPtr(m_stackAllocator.addressOf(currentBacktrackingLevel.descendantBacktrackingStart), elementAddressRegister);
2821 m_backtrackingStack.append(currentBacktrackingLevel.descendantBacktrackingStart);
2822 currentBacktrackingLevel.descendantBacktrackingStart = StackAllocator::StackReference();
2823 }
2824
2825 m_assembler.jump(m_backtrackingLevels.last().descendantEntryPoint);
2826}
2827
2828void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateBacktrackingTailsIfNeeded(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases, const SelectorFragment& fragment)
2829{
2830 if (fragment.backtrackingFlags & BacktrackingFlag::DirectAdjacentTail && fragment.backtrackingFlags & BacktrackingFlag::DescendantTail) {
2831 Assembler::Jump normalCase = m_assembler.jump();
2832 generateAdjacentBacktrackingTail();
2833 generateDescendantBacktrackingTail();
2834 normalCase.link(&m_assembler);
2835 } else if (fragment.backtrackingFlags & BacktrackingFlag::DirectAdjacentTail) {
2836 Assembler::Jump normalCase = m_assembler.jump();
2837 generateAdjacentBacktrackingTail();
2838 failureCases.append(m_assembler.jump());
2839 normalCase.link(&m_assembler);
2840 } else if (fragment.backtrackingFlags & BacktrackingFlag::DescendantTail) {
2841 Assembler::Jump normalCase = m_assembler.jump();
2842 generateDescendantBacktrackingTail();
2843 normalCase.link(&m_assembler);
2844 }
2845}
2846
2847void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateElementMatching(Assembler::JumpList& matchingTagNameFailureCases, Assembler::JumpList& matchingPostTagNameFailureCases, const SelectorFragment& fragment)
2848{
2849 if (fragment.tagNameSelector)
2850 generateElementHasTagName(matchingTagNameFailureCases, *(fragment.tagNameSelector));
2851
2852 generateElementLinkMatching(matchingPostTagNameFailureCases, fragment);
2853
2854 if (fragment.pseudoClasses.contains(CSSSelector::PseudoClassRoot))
2855 generateElementIsRoot(matchingPostTagNameFailureCases);
2856
2857 if (fragment.pseudoClasses.contains(CSSSelector::PseudoClassScope))
2858 generateElementIsScopeRoot(matchingPostTagNameFailureCases);
2859
2860 if (fragment.pseudoClasses.contains(CSSSelector::PseudoClassTarget))
2861 generateElementIsTarget(matchingPostTagNameFailureCases);
2862
2863 for (unsigned i = 0; i < fragment.unoptimizedPseudoClasses.size(); ++i)
2864 generateElementFunctionCallTest(matchingPostTagNameFailureCases, fragment.unoptimizedPseudoClasses[i]);
2865
2866 generateElementDataMatching(matchingPostTagNameFailureCases, fragment);
2867
2868 if (fragment.pseudoClasses.contains(CSSSelector::PseudoClassActive))
2869 generateElementIsActive(matchingPostTagNameFailureCases, fragment);
2870 if (fragment.pseudoClasses.contains(CSSSelector::PseudoClassEmpty))
2871 generateElementIsEmpty(matchingPostTagNameFailureCases);
2872 if (fragment.pseudoClasses.contains(CSSSelector::PseudoClassHover))
2873 generateElementIsHovered(matchingPostTagNameFailureCases, fragment);
2874 if (fragment.pseudoClasses.contains(CSSSelector::PseudoClassOnlyChild))
2875 generateElementIsOnlyChild(matchingPostTagNameFailureCases);
2876 if (fragment.pseudoClasses.contains(CSSSelector::PseudoClassPlaceholderShown))
2877 generateElementHasPlaceholderShown(matchingPostTagNameFailureCases);
2878 if (fragment.pseudoClasses.contains(CSSSelector::PseudoClassFirstChild))
2879 generateElementIsFirstChild(matchingPostTagNameFailureCases);
2880 if (fragment.pseudoClasses.contains(CSSSelector::PseudoClassLastChild))
2881 generateElementIsLastChild(matchingPostTagNameFailureCases);
2882 if (!fragment.nthChildFilters.isEmpty())
2883 generateElementIsNthChild(matchingPostTagNameFailureCases, fragment);
2884 if (!fragment.nthLastChildFilters.isEmpty())
2885 generateElementIsNthLastChild(matchingPostTagNameFailureCases, fragment);
2886 if (!fragment.notFilters.isEmpty())
2887 generateElementMatchesNotPseudoClass(matchingPostTagNameFailureCases, fragment);
2888 if (!fragment.anyFilters.isEmpty())
2889 generateElementMatchesAnyPseudoClass(matchingPostTagNameFailureCases, fragment);
2890 if (!fragment.matchesFilters.isEmpty())
2891 generateElementMatchesMatchesPseudoClass(matchingPostTagNameFailureCases, fragment);
2892 if (!fragment.languageArgumentsList.isEmpty())
2893 generateElementIsInLanguage(matchingPostTagNameFailureCases, fragment);
2894 if (!fragment.nthChildOfFilters.isEmpty())
2895 generateElementIsNthChildOf(matchingPostTagNameFailureCases, fragment);
2896 if (!fragment.nthLastChildOfFilters.isEmpty())
2897 generateElementIsNthLastChildOf(matchingPostTagNameFailureCases, fragment);
2898 if (fragment.pseudoElementSelector)
2899 generateElementHasPseudoElement(matchingPostTagNameFailureCases, fragment);
2900
2901 // Reach here when the generateElementMatching matching succeeded.
2902 // Only when the matching succeeeded, the last visited element should be stored and checked at the end of the whole matching.
2903 if (fragment.pseudoClasses.contains(CSSSelector::PseudoClassVisited))
2904 generateStoreLastVisitedElement(elementAddressRegister);
2905}
2906
2907void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateElementDataMatching(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases, const SelectorFragment& fragment)
2908{
2909 if (!fragment.id && fragment.classNames.isEmpty() && fragment.attributes.isEmpty())
2910 return;
2911
2912 // Generate:
2913 // elementDataAddress = element->elementData();
2914 // if (!elementDataAddress)
2915 // failure!
2916 LocalRegister elementDataAddress(m_registerAllocator);
2917 m_assembler.loadPtr(Assembler::Address(elementAddressRegister, Element::elementDataMemoryOffset()), elementDataAddress);
2918 failureCases.append(m_assembler.branchTestPtr(Assembler::Zero, elementDataAddress));
2919
2920 if (fragment.id)
2921 generateElementHasId(failureCases, elementDataAddress, *fragment.id);
2922 if (!fragment.classNames.isEmpty())
2923 generateElementHasClasses(failureCases, elementDataAddress, fragment.classNames);
2924 if (!fragment.attributes.isEmpty())
2925 generateElementAttributesMatching(failureCases, elementDataAddress, fragment);
2926}
2927
2928void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateElementLinkMatching(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases, const SelectorFragment& fragment)
2929{
2930 if (fragment.pseudoClasses.contains(CSSSelector::PseudoClassLink)
2931 || fragment.pseudoClasses.contains(CSSSelector::PseudoClassAnyLink)
2932 || fragment.pseudoClasses.contains(CSSSelector::PseudoClassVisited))
2933 generateElementIsLink(failureCases);
2934}
2935
2936static inline bool canMatchStyleAttribute(const SelectorFragment& fragment)
2937{
2938 for (unsigned i = 0; i < fragment.attributes.size(); ++i) {
2939 const CSSSelector& attributeSelector = fragment.attributes[i].selector();
2940 const QualifiedName& attributeName = attributeSelector.attribute();
2941 if (Attribute::nameMatchesFilter(HTMLNames::styleAttr, attributeName.prefix(), attributeName.localName(), attributeName.namespaceURI()))
2942 return true;
2943
2944 const AtomString& canonicalLocalName = attributeSelector.attributeCanonicalLocalName();
2945 if (attributeName.localName() != canonicalLocalName
2946 && Attribute::nameMatchesFilter(HTMLNames::styleAttr, attributeName.prefix(), attributeSelector.attributeCanonicalLocalName(), attributeName.namespaceURI())) {
2947 return true;
2948 }
2949 }
2950 return false;
2951}
2952
2953void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateSynchronizeStyleAttribute(Assembler::RegisterID elementDataArraySizeAndFlags)
2954{
2955 // The style attribute is updated lazily based on the flag styleAttributeIsDirty.
2956 Assembler::Jump styleAttributeNotDirty = m_assembler.branchTest32(Assembler::Zero, elementDataArraySizeAndFlags, Assembler::TrustedImm32(ElementData::styleAttributeIsDirtyFlag()));
2957
2958 FunctionCall functionCall(m_assembler, m_registerAllocator, m_stackAllocator, m_functionCalls);
2959 functionCall.setFunctionAddress(operationSynchronizeStyleAttributeInternal);
2960 Assembler::RegisterID elementAddress = elementAddressRegister;
2961 functionCall.setOneArgument(elementAddress);
2962 functionCall.call();
2963
2964 styleAttributeNotDirty.link(&m_assembler);
2965}
2966
2967static inline bool canMatchAnimatableSVGAttribute(const SelectorFragment& fragment)
2968{
2969 for (unsigned i = 0; i < fragment.attributes.size(); ++i) {
2970 const CSSSelector& attributeSelector = fragment.attributes[i].selector();
2971 const QualifiedName& selectorAttributeName = attributeSelector.attribute();
2972
2973 const QualifiedName& candidateForLocalName = SVGElement::animatableAttributeForName(selectorAttributeName.localName());
2974 if (Attribute::nameMatchesFilter(candidateForLocalName, selectorAttributeName.prefix(), selectorAttributeName.localName(), selectorAttributeName.namespaceURI()))
2975 return true;
2976
2977 const AtomString& canonicalLocalName = attributeSelector.attributeCanonicalLocalName();
2978 if (selectorAttributeName.localName() != canonicalLocalName) {
2979 const QualifiedName& candidateForCanonicalLocalName = SVGElement::animatableAttributeForName(selectorAttributeName.localName());
2980 if (Attribute::nameMatchesFilter(candidateForCanonicalLocalName, selectorAttributeName.prefix(), selectorAttributeName.localName(), selectorAttributeName.namespaceURI()))
2981 return true;
2982 }
2983 }
2984 return false;
2985}
2986
2987void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateSynchronizeAllAnimatedSVGAttribute(Assembler::RegisterID elementDataArraySizeAndFlags)
2988{
2989 // SVG attributes can be updated lazily depending on the flag AnimatedSVGAttributesAreDirty. We need to check
2990 // that first.
2991 Assembler::Jump animatedSVGAttributesNotDirty = m_assembler.branchTest32(Assembler::Zero, elementDataArraySizeAndFlags, Assembler::TrustedImm32(ElementData::animatedSVGAttributesAreDirtyFlag()));
2992
2993 FunctionCall functionCall(m_assembler, m_registerAllocator, m_stackAllocator, m_functionCalls);
2994 functionCall.setFunctionAddress(operationSynchronizeAllAnimatedSVGAttribute);
2995 Assembler::RegisterID elementAddress = elementAddressRegister;
2996 functionCall.setOneArgument(elementAddress);
2997 functionCall.call();
2998
2999 animatedSVGAttributesNotDirty.link(&m_assembler);
3000}
3001
3002void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateElementAttributesMatching(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases, const LocalRegister& elementDataAddress, const SelectorFragment& fragment)
3003{
3004 LocalRegister scratchRegister(m_registerAllocator);
3005 Assembler::RegisterID elementDataArraySizeAndFlags = scratchRegister;
3006 Assembler::RegisterID attributeArrayLength = scratchRegister;
3007
3008 m_assembler.load32(Assembler::Address(elementDataAddress, ElementData::arraySizeAndFlagsMemoryOffset()), elementDataArraySizeAndFlags);
3009
3010 if (canMatchStyleAttribute(fragment))
3011 generateSynchronizeStyleAttribute(elementDataArraySizeAndFlags);
3012
3013 if (canMatchAnimatableSVGAttribute(fragment))
3014 generateSynchronizeAllAnimatedSVGAttribute(elementDataArraySizeAndFlags);
3015
3016 // Attributes can be stored either in a separate vector for UniqueElementData, or after the elementData itself
3017 // for ShareableElementData.
3018 LocalRegister attributeArrayPointer(m_registerAllocator);
3019 Assembler::Jump isShareableElementData = m_assembler.branchTest32(Assembler::Zero, elementDataArraySizeAndFlags, Assembler::TrustedImm32(ElementData::isUniqueFlag()));
3020 {
3021 ptrdiff_t attributeVectorOffset = UniqueElementData::attributeVectorMemoryOffset();
3022 m_assembler.loadPtr(Assembler::Address(elementDataAddress, attributeVectorOffset + UniqueElementData::AttributeVector::dataMemoryOffset()), attributeArrayPointer);
3023 m_assembler.load32(Assembler::Address(elementDataAddress, attributeVectorOffset + UniqueElementData::AttributeVector::sizeMemoryOffset()), attributeArrayLength);
3024 }
3025 Assembler::Jump skipShareable = m_assembler.jump();
3026
3027 {
3028 isShareableElementData.link(&m_assembler);
3029 m_assembler.urshift32(elementDataArraySizeAndFlags, Assembler::TrustedImm32(ElementData::arraySizeOffset()), attributeArrayLength);
3030 m_assembler.addPtr(Assembler::TrustedImm32(ShareableElementData::attributeArrayMemoryOffset()), elementDataAddress, attributeArrayPointer);
3031 }
3032
3033 skipShareable.link(&m_assembler);
3034
3035 // If there are no attributes, fail immediately.
3036 failureCases.append(m_assembler.branchTest32(Assembler::Zero, attributeArrayLength));
3037
3038 unsigned attributeCount = fragment.attributes.size();
3039 for (unsigned i = 0; i < attributeCount; ++i) {
3040 Assembler::RegisterID decIndexRegister;
3041 Assembler::RegisterID currentAttributeAddress;
3042
3043 bool isLastAttribute = i == (attributeCount - 1);
3044 if (!isLastAttribute) {
3045 // We need to make a copy to let the next iterations use the values.
3046 currentAttributeAddress = m_registerAllocator.allocateRegister();
3047 decIndexRegister = m_registerAllocator.allocateRegister();
3048 m_assembler.move(attributeArrayPointer, currentAttributeAddress);
3049 m_assembler.move(attributeArrayLength, decIndexRegister);
3050 } else {
3051 currentAttributeAddress = attributeArrayPointer;
3052 decIndexRegister = attributeArrayLength;
3053 }
3054
3055 generateElementAttributeMatching(failureCases, currentAttributeAddress, decIndexRegister, fragment.attributes[i]);
3056
3057 if (!isLastAttribute) {
3058 m_registerAllocator.deallocateRegister(decIndexRegister);
3059 m_registerAllocator.deallocateRegister(currentAttributeAddress);
3060 }
3061 }
3062}
3063
3064void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateElementAttributeMatching(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases, Assembler::RegisterID currentAttributeAddress, Assembler::RegisterID decIndexRegister, const AttributeMatchingInfo& attributeInfo)
3065{
3066 // Get the localName used for comparison. HTML elements use a lowercase local name known in selectors as canonicalLocalName.
3067 LocalRegister localNameToMatch(m_registerAllocator);
3068
3069 // In general, canonicalLocalName and localName are the same. When they differ, we have to check if the node is HTML to know
3070 // which one to use.
3071 const CSSSelector& attributeSelector = attributeInfo.selector();
3072 const AtomStringImpl* canonicalLocalName = attributeSelector.attributeCanonicalLocalName().impl();
3073 const AtomStringImpl* localName = attributeSelector.attribute().localName().impl();
3074 if (canonicalLocalName == localName)
3075 m_assembler.move(Assembler::TrustedImmPtr(canonicalLocalName), localNameToMatch);
3076 else {
3077 m_assembler.move(Assembler::TrustedImmPtr(canonicalLocalName), localNameToMatch);
3078 Assembler::Jump elementIsHTML = DOMJIT::branchTestIsHTMLFlagOnNode(m_assembler, Assembler::NonZero, elementAddressRegister);
3079 m_assembler.move(Assembler::TrustedImmPtr(localName), localNameToMatch);
3080 elementIsHTML.link(&m_assembler);
3081 }
3082
3083 Assembler::JumpList successCases;
3084 Assembler::Label loopStart(m_assembler.label());
3085
3086 {
3087 LocalRegister qualifiedNameImpl(m_registerAllocator);
3088 m_assembler.loadPtr(Assembler::Address(currentAttributeAddress, Attribute::nameMemoryOffset()), qualifiedNameImpl);
3089
3090 bool shouldCheckNamespace = attributeSelector.attribute().prefix() != starAtom();
3091 if (shouldCheckNamespace) {
3092 Assembler::Jump nameDoesNotMatch = m_assembler.branchPtr(Assembler::NotEqual, Assembler::Address(qualifiedNameImpl, QualifiedName::QualifiedNameImpl::localNameMemoryOffset()), localNameToMatch);
3093
3094 const AtomStringImpl* namespaceURI = attributeSelector.attribute().namespaceURI().impl();
3095 if (namespaceURI) {
3096 LocalRegister namespaceToMatch(m_registerAllocator);
3097 m_assembler.move(Assembler::TrustedImmPtr(namespaceURI), namespaceToMatch);
3098 successCases.append(m_assembler.branchPtr(Assembler::Equal, Assembler::Address(qualifiedNameImpl, QualifiedName::QualifiedNameImpl::namespaceMemoryOffset()), namespaceToMatch));
3099 } else
3100 successCases.append(m_assembler.branchTestPtr(Assembler::Zero, Assembler::Address(qualifiedNameImpl, QualifiedName::QualifiedNameImpl::namespaceMemoryOffset())));
3101 nameDoesNotMatch.link(&m_assembler);
3102 } else
3103 successCases.append(m_assembler.branchPtr(Assembler::Equal, Assembler::Address(qualifiedNameImpl, QualifiedName::QualifiedNameImpl::localNameMemoryOffset()), localNameToMatch));
3104 }
3105
3106 Assembler::Label loopReEntry(m_assembler.label());
3107
3108 // If we reached the last element -> failure.
3109 failureCases.append(m_assembler.branchSub32(Assembler::Zero, Assembler::TrustedImm32(1), decIndexRegister));
3110
3111 // Otherwise just loop over.
3112 m_assembler.addPtr(Assembler::TrustedImm32(sizeof(Attribute)), currentAttributeAddress);
3113 m_assembler.jump().linkTo(loopStart, &m_assembler);
3114
3115 successCases.link(&m_assembler);
3116
3117 if (attributeSelector.match() != CSSSelector::Set) {
3118 // We make the assumption that name matching fails in most cases and we keep value matching outside
3119 // of the loop. We re-enter the loop if needed.
3120 // FIXME: exact case sensitive value matching is so simple that it should be done in the loop.
3121 Assembler::JumpList localFailureCases;
3122 generateElementAttributeValueMatching(localFailureCases, currentAttributeAddress, attributeInfo);
3123 localFailureCases.linkTo(loopReEntry, &m_assembler);
3124 }
3125}
3126
3127enum CaseSensitivity {
3128 CaseSensitive,
3129 CaseInsensitive
3130};
3131
3132template<CaseSensitivity caseSensitivity>
3133static bool attributeValueBeginsWith(const Attribute* attribute, AtomStringImpl* expectedString)
3134{
3135 ASSERT(expectedString);
3136
3137 AtomStringImpl& valueImpl = *attribute->value().impl();
3138 if (caseSensitivity == CaseSensitive)
3139 return valueImpl.startsWith(*expectedString);
3140 return valueImpl.startsWithIgnoringASCIICase(*expectedString);
3141}
3142
3143template<CaseSensitivity caseSensitivity>
3144static bool attributeValueContains(const Attribute* attribute, AtomStringImpl* expectedString)
3145{
3146 AtomStringImpl& valueImpl = *attribute->value().impl();
3147 if (caseSensitivity == CaseSensitive)
3148 return valueImpl.find(expectedString) != notFound;
3149 return valueImpl.findIgnoringASCIICase(expectedString) != notFound;
3150}
3151
3152template<CaseSensitivity caseSensitivity>
3153static bool attributeValueEndsWith(const Attribute* attribute, AtomStringImpl* expectedString)
3154{
3155 ASSERT(expectedString);
3156
3157 AtomStringImpl& valueImpl = *attribute->value().impl();
3158 if (caseSensitivity == CaseSensitive)
3159 return valueImpl.endsWith(*expectedString);
3160 return valueImpl.endsWithIgnoringASCIICase(*expectedString);
3161}
3162
3163template<CaseSensitivity caseSensitivity>
3164static bool attributeValueMatchHyphenRule(const Attribute* attribute, AtomStringImpl* expectedString)
3165{
3166 ASSERT(expectedString);
3167
3168 AtomStringImpl& valueImpl = *attribute->value().impl();
3169 if (valueImpl.length() < expectedString->length())
3170 return false;
3171
3172 bool valueStartsWithExpectedString;
3173 if (caseSensitivity == CaseSensitive)
3174 valueStartsWithExpectedString = valueImpl.startsWith(*expectedString);
3175 else
3176 valueStartsWithExpectedString = valueImpl.startsWithIgnoringASCIICase(*expectedString);
3177
3178 if (!valueStartsWithExpectedString)
3179 return false;
3180
3181 return valueImpl.length() == expectedString->length() || valueImpl[expectedString->length()] == '-';
3182}
3183
3184template<CaseSensitivity caseSensitivity>
3185static bool attributeValueSpaceSeparatedListContains(const Attribute* attribute, AtomStringImpl* expectedString)
3186{
3187 AtomStringImpl& value = *attribute->value().impl();
3188
3189 unsigned startSearchAt = 0;
3190 while (true) {
3191 size_t foundPos;
3192 if (caseSensitivity == CaseSensitive)
3193 foundPos = value.find(expectedString, startSearchAt);
3194 else
3195 foundPos = value.findIgnoringASCIICase(expectedString, startSearchAt);
3196 if (foundPos == notFound)
3197 return false;
3198 if (!foundPos || isHTMLSpace(value[foundPos - 1])) {
3199 unsigned endStr = foundPos + expectedString->length();
3200 if (endStr == value.length() || isHTMLSpace(value[endStr]))
3201 return true;
3202 }
3203 startSearchAt = foundPos + 1;
3204 }
3205 return false;
3206}

3257
3258void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateElementAttributeValueMatching(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases, Assembler::RegisterID currentAttributeAddress, const AttributeMatchingInfo& attributeInfo)
3259{
3260 const CSSSelector& attributeSelector = attributeInfo.selector();
3261 const AtomString& expectedValue = attributeSelector.value();
3262 ASSERT(!expectedValue.isNull());
3263 AttributeCaseSensitivity valueCaseSensitivity = attributeInfo.attributeCaseSensitivity();
3264
3265 switch (attributeSelector.match()) {
3266 case CSSSelector::Begin:
3267 generateElementAttributeFunctionCallValueMatching(failureCases, currentAttributeAddress, expectedValue, valueCaseSensitivity, operationAttributeValueBeginsWithCaseSensitive, operationAttributeValueBeginsWithCaseInsensitive);
3268 break;
3269 case CSSSelector::Contain:
3270 generateElementAttributeFunctionCallValueMatching(failureCases, currentAttributeAddress, expectedValue, valueCaseSensitivity, operationAttributeValueContainsCaseSensitive, operationAttributeValueContainsCaseInsensitive);
3271 break;
3272 case CSSSelector::End:
3273 generateElementAttributeFunctionCallValueMatching(failureCases, currentAttributeAddress, expectedValue, valueCaseSensitivity, operationAttributeValueEndsWithCaseSensitive, operationAttributeValueEndsWithCaseInsensitive);
3274 break;
3275 case CSSSelector::Exact:
3276 generateElementAttributeValueExactMatching(failureCases, currentAttributeAddress, expectedValue, valueCaseSensitivity);
3277 break;
3278 case CSSSelector::Hyphen:
3279 generateElementAttributeFunctionCallValueMatching(failureCases, currentAttributeAddress, expectedValue, valueCaseSensitivity, operationAttributeValueMatchHyphenRuleCaseSensitive, operationAttributeValueMatchHyphenRuleCaseInsensitive);
3280 break;
3281 case CSSSelector::List:
3282 generateElementAttributeFunctionCallValueMatching(failureCases, currentAttributeAddress, expectedValue, valueCaseSensitivity, operationAttributeValueSpaceSeparatedListContainsCaseSensitive, operationAttributeValueSpaceSeparatedListContainsCaseInsensitive);
3283 break;
3284 default:
3285 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
3286 }
3287}
3288
3289static inline Assembler::Jump testIsHTMLClassOnDocument(Assembler::ResultCondition condition, Assembler& assembler, Assembler::RegisterID documentAddress)
3290{
3291 return assembler.branchTest32(condition, Assembler::Address(documentAddress, Document::documentClassesMemoryOffset()), Assembler::TrustedImm32(Document::isHTMLDocumentClassFlag()));
3292}
3293
3294void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateElementAttributeValueExactMatching(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases, Assembler::RegisterID currentAttributeAddress, const AtomString& expectedValue, AttributeCaseSensitivity valueCaseSensitivity)
3295{
3296 LocalRegisterWithPreference expectedValueRegister(m_registerAllocator, JSC::GPRInfo::argumentGPR1);
3297 m_assembler.move(Assembler::TrustedImmPtr(expectedValue.impl()), expectedValueRegister);
3298
3299 switch (valueCaseSensitivity) {
3300 case AttributeCaseSensitivity::CaseSensitive: {
3301 failureCases.append(m_assembler.branchPtr(Assembler::NotEqual, Assembler::Address(currentAttributeAddress, Attribute::valueMemoryOffset()), expectedValueRegister));
3302 break;
3303 }
3304 case AttributeCaseSensitivity::HTMLLegacyCaseInsensitive: {
3305 Assembler::Jump skipCaseInsensitiveComparison = m_assembler.branchPtr(Assembler::Equal, Assembler::Address(currentAttributeAddress, Attribute::valueMemoryOffset()), expectedValueRegister);
3306
3307 // If the element is an HTML element, in a HTML dcoument (not including XHTML), value matching is case insensitive.
3308 // Taking the contrapositive, if we find the element is not HTML or is not in a HTML document, the condition above
3309 // sould be sufficient and we can fail early.
3310 failureCases.append(DOMJIT::branchTestIsHTMLFlagOnNode(m_assembler, Assembler::Zero, elementAddressRegister));
3311
3312 {
3313 LocalRegister document(m_registerAllocator);
3314 DOMJIT::loadDocument(m_assembler, elementAddressRegister, document);
3315 failureCases.append(testIsHTMLClassOnDocument(Assembler::Zero, m_assembler, document));
3316 }
3317
3318 LocalRegister valueStringImpl(m_registerAllocator);
3319 m_assembler.loadPtr(Assembler::Address(currentAttributeAddress, Attribute::valueMemoryOffset()), valueStringImpl);
3320
3321 FunctionCall functionCall(m_assembler, m_registerAllocator, m_stackAllocator, m_functionCalls);
3322 functionCall.setFunctionAddress(operationEqualIgnoringASCIICaseNonNull);
3323 functionCall.setTwoArguments(valueStringImpl, expectedValueRegister);
3324 failureCases.append(functionCall.callAndBranchOnBooleanReturnValue(Assembler::Zero));
3325
3326 skipCaseInsensitiveComparison.link(&m_assembler);
3327 break;
3328 }
3329 case AttributeCaseSensitivity::CaseInsensitive: {
3330 LocalRegister valueStringImpl(m_registerAllocator);
3331 m_assembler.loadPtr(Assembler::Address(currentAttributeAddress, Attribute::valueMemoryOffset()), valueStringImpl);
3332
3333 Assembler::Jump skipCaseInsensitiveComparison = m_assembler.branchPtr(Assembler::Equal, valueStringImpl, expectedValueRegister);
3334 FunctionCall functionCall(m_assembler, m_registerAllocator, m_stackAllocator, m_functionCalls);
3335 functionCall.setFunctionAddress(operationEqualIgnoringASCIICaseNonNull);
3336 functionCall.setTwoArguments(valueStringImpl, expectedValueRegister);
3337 failureCases.append(functionCall.callAndBranchOnBooleanReturnValue(Assembler::Zero));
3338 skipCaseInsensitiveComparison.link(&m_assembler);
3339 break;
3340 }
3341 }
3342}

3344void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateElementAttributeFunctionCallValueMatching(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases, Assembler::RegisterID currentAttributeAddress, const AtomString& expectedValue, AttributeCaseSensitivity valueCaseSensitivity, JSC::FunctionPtr<JSC::OperationPtrTag> caseSensitiveTest, JSC::FunctionPtr<JSC::OperationPtrTag> caseInsensitiveTest)
3345{
3346 LocalRegisterWithPreference expectedValueRegister(m_registerAllocator, JSC::GPRInfo::argumentGPR1);
3347 m_assembler.move(Assembler::TrustedImmPtr(expectedValue.impl()), expectedValueRegister);
3348
3349
3350 switch (valueCaseSensitivity) {
3351 case AttributeCaseSensitivity::CaseSensitive: {
3352 FunctionCall functionCall(m_assembler, m_registerAllocator, m_stackAllocator, m_functionCalls);
3353 functionCall.setFunctionAddress(caseSensitiveTest);
3354 functionCall.setTwoArguments(currentAttributeAddress, expectedValueRegister);
3355 failureCases.append(functionCall.callAndBranchOnBooleanReturnValue(Assembler::Zero));
3356 break;
3357 }
3358 case AttributeCaseSensitivity::HTMLLegacyCaseInsensitive: {
3359 Assembler::JumpList shouldUseCaseSensitiveComparison;
3360 shouldUseCaseSensitiveComparison.append(DOMJIT::branchTestIsHTMLFlagOnNode(m_assembler, Assembler::Zero, elementAddressRegister));
3361 {
3362 LocalRegister scratchRegister(m_registerAllocator);
3363 // scratchRegister = pointer to treeScope.
3364 m_assembler.loadPtr(Assembler::Address(elementAddressRegister, Node::treeScopeMemoryOffset()), scratchRegister);
3365 // scratchRegister = pointer to document.
3366 m_assembler.loadPtr(Assembler::Address(scratchRegister, TreeScope::documentScopeMemoryOffset()), scratchRegister);
3367 shouldUseCaseSensitiveComparison.append(testIsHTMLClassOnDocument(Assembler::Zero, m_assembler, scratchRegister));
3368 }
3369
3370 {
3371 FunctionCall functionCall(m_assembler, m_registerAllocator, m_stackAllocator, m_functionCalls);
3372 functionCall.setFunctionAddress(caseInsensitiveTest);
3373 functionCall.setTwoArguments(currentAttributeAddress, expectedValueRegister);
3374 failureCases.append(functionCall.callAndBranchOnBooleanReturnValue(Assembler::Zero));
3375 }
3376
3377 Assembler::Jump skipCaseSensitiveCase = m_assembler.jump();
3378
3379 {
3380 shouldUseCaseSensitiveComparison.link(&m_assembler);
3381 FunctionCall functionCall(m_assembler, m_registerAllocator, m_stackAllocator, m_functionCalls);
3382 functionCall.setFunctionAddress(caseSensitiveTest);
3383 functionCall.setTwoArguments(currentAttributeAddress, expectedValueRegister);
3384 failureCases.append(functionCall.callAndBranchOnBooleanReturnValue(Assembler::Zero));
3385 }
3386
3387 skipCaseSensitiveCase.link(&m_assembler);
3388 break;
3389 }
3390 case AttributeCaseSensitivity::CaseInsensitive: {
3391 FunctionCall functionCall(m_assembler, m_registerAllocator, m_stackAllocator, m_functionCalls);
3392 functionCall.setFunctionAddress(caseInsensitiveTest);
3393 functionCall.setTwoArguments(currentAttributeAddress, expectedValueRegister);
3394 failureCases.append(functionCall.callAndBranchOnBooleanReturnValue(Assembler::Zero));
3395 break;
3396 }
3397 }
3398}

3404 functionCall.setFunctionAddress(testFunction);

3406 failureCases.append(functionCall.callAndBranchOnBooleanReturnValue(Assembler::Zero));

3424static void jumpIfElementIsNotEmpty(Assembler& assembler, RegisterAllocator& registerAllocator, Assembler::JumpList& notEmptyCases, Assembler::RegisterID element)
3425{
3426 LocalRegister currentChild(registerAllocator);
3427 assembler.loadPtr(Assembler::Address(element, ContainerNode::firstChildMemoryOffset()), currentChild);
3428
3429 Assembler::Label loopStart(assembler.label());
3430 Assembler::Jump noMoreChildren = assembler.branchTestPtr(Assembler::Zero, currentChild);
3431
3432 notEmptyCases.append(DOMJIT::branchTestIsElementFlagOnNode(assembler, Assembler::NonZero, currentChild));
3433
3434 {
3435 Assembler::Jump skipTextNodeCheck = assembler.branchTest32(Assembler::Zero, Assembler::Address(currentChild, Node::nodeFlagsMemoryOffset()), Assembler::TrustedImm32(Node::flagIsText()));
3436
3437 LocalRegister textStringImpl(registerAllocator);
3438 assembler.loadPtr(Assembler::Address(currentChild, CharacterData::dataMemoryOffset()), textStringImpl);
3439 notEmptyCases.append(assembler.branchTest32(Assembler::NonZero, Assembler::Address(textStringImpl, StringImpl::lengthMemoryOffset())));
3440
3441 skipTextNodeCheck.link(&assembler);
3442 }
3443
3444 assembler.loadPtr(Assembler::Address(currentChild, Node::nextSiblingMemoryOffset()), currentChild);
3445 assembler.jump().linkTo(loopStart, &assembler);
3446
3447 noMoreChildren.link(&assembler);
3448}

3450void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateElementIsEmpty(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases)
3451{
3452 if (m_selectorContext == SelectorContext::QuerySelector) {
3453 jumpIfElementIsNotEmpty(m_assembler, m_registerAllocator, failureCases, elementAddressRegister);
3454 return;
3455 }
3456
3457 LocalRegisterWithPreference isEmptyResults(m_registerAllocator, JSC::GPRInfo::argumentGPR1);
3458 m_assembler.move(Assembler::TrustedImm32(0), isEmptyResults);
3459
3460 Assembler::JumpList notEmpty;
3461 jumpIfElementIsNotEmpty(m_assembler, m_registerAllocator, notEmpty, elementAddressRegister);
3462 m_assembler.move(Assembler::TrustedImm32(1), isEmptyResults);
3463 notEmpty.link(&m_assembler);
3464
3465 generateAddStyleRelationIfResolvingStyle(elementAddressRegister, Style::Relation::AffectedByEmpty, Assembler::RegisterID(isEmptyResults));
3466
3467 failureCases.append(m_assembler.branchTest32(Assembler::Zero, isEmptyResults));
3468}

3470void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateElementIsFirstChild(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases)
3471{
3472 if (m_selectorContext == SelectorContext::QuerySelector) {
3473 Assembler::JumpList successCase = jumpIfNoPreviousAdjacentElement();
3474 failureCases.append(m_assembler.jump());
3475 successCase.link(&m_assembler);
3476 LocalRegister parent(m_registerAllocator);
3477 generateWalkToParentElementOrShadowRoot(failureCases, parent);
3478 return;
3479 }
3480
3481 // Zero in isFirstChildRegister is the success case. The register is set to non-zero if a sibling if found.
3482 LocalRegister isFirstChildRegister(m_registerAllocator);
3483 m_assembler.move(Assembler::TrustedImm32(0), isFirstChildRegister);
3484
3485 {
3486 Assembler::JumpList successCase = jumpIfNoPreviousAdjacentElement();
3487
3488 // If there was a sibling element, the element was not the first child -> failure case.
3489 m_assembler.move(Assembler::TrustedImm32(1), isFirstChildRegister);
3490
3491 successCase.link(&m_assembler);
3492 }
3493
3494 LocalRegister parentNode(m_registerAllocator);
3495 generateWalkToParentNode(parentNode);
3496 failureCases.append(m_assembler.branchTestPtr(Assembler::Zero, parentNode));
3497 Assembler::Jump notElement = DOMJIT::branchTestIsElementFlagOnNode(m_assembler, Assembler::Zero, parentNode);
3498
3499 LocalRegister checkingContext(m_registerAllocator);
3500 Assembler::Jump notResolvingStyle = jumpIfNotResolvingStyle(checkingContext);
3501
3502 generateAddStyleRelation(checkingContext, parentNode, Style::Relation::ChildrenAffectedByFirstChildRules);
3503 // The parent marking is unconditional. If the matching is not a success, we can now fail.
3504 // Otherwise we need to apply setFirstChildState() on the RenderStyle.
3505 Assembler::Label checkWithRelation(m_assembler.label());
3506 failureCases.append(m_assembler.branchTest32(Assembler::NonZero, isFirstChildRegister));
3507 generateAddStyleRelation(checkingContext, elementAddressRegister, Style::Relation::FirstChild);
3508 Assembler::Jump successCase = m_assembler.jump();
3509
3510 notElement.link(&m_assembler);
3511 failureCases.append(DOMJIT::branchTestIsShadowRootFlagOnNode(m_assembler, Assembler::Zero, parentNode));
3512 jumpIfNotResolvingStyle(checkingContext).linkTo(checkWithRelation, &m_assembler);
3513
3514 notResolvingStyle.link(&m_assembler);
3515 failureCases.append(m_assembler.branchTest32(Assembler::NonZero, isFirstChildRegister));
3516
3517 successCase.link(&m_assembler);
3518}

3553void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateElementIsLastChild(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases)
3554{
3555 if (m_selectorContext == SelectorContext::QuerySelector) {
3556 Assembler::JumpList successCase = jumpIfNoNextAdjacentElement();
3557 failureCases.append(m_assembler.jump());
3558
3559 successCase.link(&m_assembler);
3560 LocalRegister parent(m_registerAllocator);
3561 generateWalkToParentElementOrShadowRoot(failureCases, parent);
3562
3563 failureCases.append(m_assembler.branchTest32(Assembler::Zero, Assembler::Address(parent, Node::nodeFlagsMemoryOffset()), Assembler::TrustedImm32(Node::flagIsParsingChildrenFinished())));
3564
3565 return;
3566 }
3567
3568 LocalRegister parentNode(m_registerAllocator);
3569 generateWalkToParentNode(parentNode);
3570 failureCases.append(m_assembler.branchTestPtr(Assembler::Zero, parentNode));
3571
3572 // Zero in isLastChildRegister is the success case. The register is set to non-zero if a sibling if found.
3573 LocalRegister isLastChildRegister(m_registerAllocator);
3574 m_assembler.move(Assembler::TrustedImm32(0), isLastChildRegister);
3575
3576 {
3577 Assembler::Jump notFinishedParsingChildren = m_assembler.branchTest32(Assembler::Zero, Assembler::Address(parentNode, Node::nodeFlagsMemoryOffset()), Assembler::TrustedImm32(Node::flagIsParsingChildrenFinished()));
3578
3579 Assembler::JumpList successCase = jumpIfNoNextAdjacentElement();
3580
3581 notFinishedParsingChildren.link(&m_assembler);
3582 m_assembler.move(Assembler::TrustedImm32(1), isLastChildRegister);
3583
3584 successCase.link(&m_assembler);
3585 }

3587 Assembler::Jump notElement = DOMJIT::branchTestIsElementFlagOnNode(m_assembler, Assembler::Zero, parentNode);
3588

3590 Assembler::Jump notResolvingStyle = jumpIfNotResolvingStyle(checkingContext);
3591

3593 // The parent marking is unconditional. If the matching is not a success, we can now fail.
3594 // Otherwise we need to apply setLastChildState() on the RenderStyle.
3595 Assembler::Label checkWithRelation(m_assembler.label());
3596 failureCases.append(m_assembler.branchTest32(Assembler::NonZero, isLastChildRegister));
3597 generateAddStyleRelation(checkingContext, elementAddressRegister, Style::Relation::LastChild);
3598 Assembler::Jump successCase = m_assembler.jump();
3599
3600 notElement.link(&m_assembler);
3601 failureCases.append(DOMJIT::branchTestIsShadowRootFlagOnNode(m_assembler, Assembler::Zero, parentNode));
3602 jumpIfNotResolvingStyle(checkingContext).linkTo(checkWithRelation, &m_assembler);
3603
3604 notResolvingStyle.link(&m_assembler);
3605 failureCases.append(m_assembler.branchTest32(Assembler::NonZero, isLastChildRegister));

3607 successCase.link(&m_assembler);

3609
3610void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateElementIsOnlyChild(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases)
3611{
3612 // Is Only child is pretty much a combination of isFirstChild + isLastChild. The main difference is that tree marking is combined.
3613 if (m_selectorContext == SelectorContext::QuerySelector) {
3614 Assembler::JumpList previousSuccessCase = jumpIfNoPreviousAdjacentElement();
3615 failureCases.append(m_assembler.jump());
3616 previousSuccessCase.link(&m_assembler);
3617
3618 Assembler::JumpList nextSuccessCase = jumpIfNoNextAdjacentElement();
3619 failureCases.append(m_assembler.jump());
3620 nextSuccessCase.link(&m_assembler);
3621
3622 LocalRegister parent(m_registerAllocator);
3623 generateWalkToParentElementOrShadowRoot(failureCases, parent);
3624
3625 failureCases.append(m_assembler.branchTest32(Assembler::Zero, Assembler::Address(parent, Node::nodeFlagsMemoryOffset()), Assembler::TrustedImm32(Node::flagIsParsingChildrenFinished())));
3626
3627 return;
3628 }
3629
3630 LocalRegister parentNode(m_registerAllocator);
3631 generateWalkToParentNode(parentNode);
3632 failureCases.append(m_assembler.branchTestPtr(Assembler::Zero, parentNode));
3633
3634 // Zero in isOnlyChildRegister is the success case. The register is set to non-zero if a sibling if found.
3635 LocalRegister isOnlyChildRegister(m_registerAllocator);
3636 m_assembler.move(Assembler::TrustedImm32(0), isOnlyChildRegister);
3637
3638 {
3639 Assembler::JumpList localFailureCases;
3640 {
3641 Assembler::JumpList successCase = jumpIfNoPreviousAdjacentElement();
3642 localFailureCases.append(m_assembler.jump());
3643 successCase.link(&m_assembler);
3644 }
3645 localFailureCases.append(m_assembler.branchTest32(Assembler::Zero, Assembler::Address(parentNode, Node::nodeFlagsMemoryOffset()), Assembler::TrustedImm32(Node::flagIsParsingChildrenFinished())));
3646 Assembler::JumpList successCase = jumpIfNoNextAdjacentElement();
3647
3648 localFailureCases.link(&m_assembler);
3649 m_assembler.move(Assembler::TrustedImm32(1), isOnlyChildRegister);
3650
3651 successCase.link(&m_assembler);
3652 }
3653
3654 Assembler::Jump notElement = DOMJIT::branchTestIsElementFlagOnNode(m_assembler, Assembler::Zero, parentNode);
3655
3656 LocalRegister checkingContext(m_registerAllocator);
3657 Assembler::Jump notResolvingStyle = jumpIfNotResolvingStyle(checkingContext);
3658
3659 generateAddStyleRelation(checkingContext, parentNode, Style::Relation::ChildrenAffectedByFirstChildRules);
3660 generateAddStyleRelation(checkingContext, parentNode, Style::Relation::ChildrenAffectedByLastChildRules);
3661 // The parent marking is unconditional. If the matching is not a success, we can now fail.
3662 // Otherwise we need to apply setLastChildState() on the RenderStyle.
3663 Assembler::Label checkWithRelation(m_assembler.label());
3664 failureCases.append(m_assembler.branchTest32(Assembler::NonZero, isOnlyChildRegister));
3665 generateAddStyleRelation(checkingContext, elementAddressRegister, Style::Relation::FirstChild);
3666 generateAddStyleRelation(checkingContext, elementAddressRegister, Style::Relation::LastChild);
3667 Assembler::Jump successCase = m_assembler.jump();
3668
3669 notElement.link(&m_assembler);
3670 failureCases.append(DOMJIT::branchTestIsShadowRootFlagOnNode(m_assembler, Assembler::Zero, parentNode));
3671 jumpIfNotResolvingStyle(checkingContext).linkTo(checkWithRelation, &m_assembler);
3672
3673 notResolvingStyle.link(&m_assembler);
3674 failureCases.append(m_assembler.branchTest32(Assembler::NonZero, isOnlyChildRegister));
3675
3676 successCase.link(&m_assembler);
3677}
3678
3679JSC_DEFINE_JIT_OPERATION(operationMakeContextStyleUniqueIfNecessaryAndTestIsPlaceholderShown, bool, (const Element* element, SelectorChecker::CheckingContext* checkingContext))
3680{
3681 if (is<HTMLTextFormControlElement>(*element) && element->isTextField()) {
3682 if (checkingContext->resolvingMode == SelectorChecker::Mode::ResolvingStyle)
3683 checkingContext->styleRelations.append({ *element, Style::Relation::Unique, 1 });
3684 return downcast<HTMLTextFormControlElement>(*element).isPlaceholderVisible();
3685 }
3686 return false;
3687}
3688
3689JSC_DEFINE_JIT_OPERATION(operationIsPlaceholderShown, bool, (const Element* element))
3690{
3691 return is<HTMLTextFormControlElement>(*element) && downcast<HTMLTextFormControlElement>(*element).isPlaceholderVisible();
3692}
3693
3694JSC_DEFINE_JIT_OPERATION(operationSynchronizeStyleAttributeInternal, void, (StyledElement* styledElement))
3695{
3696 styledElement->synchronizeStyleAttributeInternal();
3697}
3698
3699JSC_DEFINE_JIT_OPERATION(operationSynchronizeAllAnimatedSVGAttribute, void, (SVGElement& element))
3700{
3701 element.synchronizeAllAttributes();
3702}
3703
3704JSC_DEFINE_JIT_OPERATION(operationEqualIgnoringASCIICaseNonNull, bool, (const StringImpl* a, const StringImpl* b))
3705{
3706 return WTF::equalIgnoringASCIICaseNonNull(a, b);
3707}
3708
3709void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateElementHasPlaceholderShown(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases)
3710{
3711 if (m_selectorContext == SelectorContext::QuerySelector) {
3712 FunctionCall functionCall(m_assembler, m_registerAllocator, m_stackAllocator, m_functionCalls);
3713 functionCall.setFunctionAddress(operationIsPlaceholderShown);
3714 functionCall.setOneArgument(elementAddressRegister);
3715 failureCases.append(functionCall.callAndBranchOnBooleanReturnValue(Assembler::Zero));
3716 return;
3717 }
3718
3719 Assembler::RegisterID checkingContext = m_registerAllocator.allocateRegisterWithPreference(JSC::GPRInfo::argumentGPR1);
3720 loadCheckingContext(checkingContext);
3721 m_registerAllocator.deallocateRegister(checkingContext);
3722
3723 FunctionCall functionCall(m_assembler, m_registerAllocator, m_stackAllocator, m_functionCalls);
3724 functionCall.setFunctionAddress(operationMakeContextStyleUniqueIfNecessaryAndTestIsPlaceholderShown);
3725 functionCall.setTwoArguments(elementAddressRegister, checkingContext);
3726 failureCases.append(functionCall.callAndBranchOnBooleanReturnValue(Assembler::Zero));
3727}
3728
3729inline void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateElementHasTagName(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases, const CSSSelector& tagMatchingSelector)
3730{
3731 const QualifiedName& nameToMatch = tagMatchingSelector.tagQName();
3732 if (nameToMatch == anyQName())
3733 return;
3734
3735 // Load the QualifiedNameImpl from the input.
3736 LocalRegister qualifiedNameImpl(m_registerAllocator);
3737 m_assembler.loadPtr(Assembler::Address(elementAddressRegister, Element::tagQNameMemoryOffset() + QualifiedName::implMemoryOffset()), qualifiedNameImpl);
3738
3739 const AtomString& selectorLocalName = nameToMatch.localName();
3740 if (selectorLocalName != starAtom()) {
3741 const AtomString& lowercaseLocalName = tagMatchingSelector.tagLowercaseLocalName();
3742
3743 if (selectorLocalName == lowercaseLocalName) {
3744 // Generate localName == element->localName().
3745 LocalRegister constantRegister(m_registerAllocator);
3746 m_assembler.move(Assembler::TrustedImmPtr(selectorLocalName.impl()), constantRegister);
3747 failureCases.append(m_assembler.branchPtr(Assembler::NotEqual, Assembler::Address(qualifiedNameImpl, QualifiedName::QualifiedNameImpl::localNameMemoryOffset()), constantRegister));
3748 } else {
3749 Assembler::JumpList caseSensitiveCases;
3750 caseSensitiveCases.append(DOMJIT::branchTestIsHTMLFlagOnNode(m_assembler, Assembler::Zero, elementAddressRegister));
3751 {
3752 LocalRegister document(m_registerAllocator);
3753 DOMJIT::loadDocument(m_assembler, elementAddressRegister, document);
3754 caseSensitiveCases.append(testIsHTMLClassOnDocument(Assembler::Zero, m_assembler, document));
3755 }
3756
3757 LocalRegister constantRegister(m_registerAllocator);
3758 m_assembler.move(Assembler::TrustedImmPtr(lowercaseLocalName.impl()), constantRegister);
3759 Assembler::Jump skipCaseSensitiveCase = m_assembler.jump();
3760
3761 caseSensitiveCases.link(&m_assembler);
3762 m_assembler.move(Assembler::TrustedImmPtr(selectorLocalName.impl()), constantRegister);
3763 skipCaseSensitiveCase.link(&m_assembler);
3764
3765 failureCases.append(m_assembler.branchPtr(Assembler::NotEqual, Assembler::Address(qualifiedNameImpl, QualifiedName::QualifiedNameImpl::localNameMemoryOffset()), constantRegister));
3766 }
3767 }
3768
3769 const AtomString& selectorNamespaceURI = nameToMatch.namespaceURI();
3770 if (selectorNamespaceURI != starAtom()) {
3771 // Generate namespaceURI == element->namespaceURI().
3772 LocalRegister constantRegister(m_registerAllocator);
3773 m_assembler.move(Assembler::TrustedImmPtr(selectorNamespaceURI.impl()), constantRegister);
3774 failureCases.append(m_assembler.branchPtr(Assembler::NotEqual, Assembler::Address(qualifiedNameImpl, QualifiedName::QualifiedNameImpl::namespaceMemoryOffset()), constantRegister));
3775 }
3776}

3778void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateElementHasId(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases, const LocalRegister& elementDataAddress, const AtomString& idToMatch)
3779{
3780 // Compare the pointers of the AtomStringImpl from idForStyleResolution with the reference idToMatch.
3781 LocalRegister idToMatchRegister(m_registerAllocator);
3782 m_assembler.move(Assembler::TrustedImmPtr(idToMatch.impl()), idToMatchRegister);
3783 failureCases.append(m_assembler.branchPtr(Assembler::NotEqual, Assembler::Address(elementDataAddress, ElementData::idForStyleResolutionMemoryOffset()), idToMatchRegister));
3784}
3785
3786void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateElementHasClasses(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases, const LocalRegister& elementDataAddress, const Vector<const AtomStringImpl*, 8>& classNames)
3787{
3788 // Load m_classNames.
3789 LocalRegister spaceSplitStringData(m_registerAllocator);
3790 m_assembler.loadPtr(Assembler::Address(elementDataAddress, ElementData::classNamesMemoryOffset()), spaceSplitStringData);
3791
3792 // If SpaceSplitString does not have a SpaceSplitStringData pointer, it is empty -> failure case.
3793 failureCases.append(m_assembler.branchTestPtr(Assembler::Zero, spaceSplitStringData));
3794
3795 // We loop over the classes of SpaceSplitStringData for each class name we need to match.
3796 LocalRegister indexRegister(m_registerAllocator);
3797 for (unsigned i = 0; i < classNames.size(); ++i) {
3798 LocalRegister classNameToMatch(m_registerAllocator);
3799 m_assembler.move(Assembler::TrustedImmPtr(classNames[i]), classNameToMatch);
3800 m_assembler.move(Assembler::TrustedImm32(0), indexRegister);
3801
3802 // Beginning of a loop over all the class name of element to find the one we are looking for.
3803 Assembler::Label loopStart(m_assembler.label());
3804
3805 // If the pointers match, proceed to the next matcher.
3806 Assembler::Jump classFound = m_assembler.branchPtr(Assembler::Equal, Assembler::BaseIndex(spaceSplitStringData, indexRegister, Assembler::ScalePtr, SpaceSplitStringData::tokensMemoryOffset()), classNameToMatch);
3807
3808 // Increment the index.
3809 m_assembler.add32(Assembler::TrustedImm32(1), indexRegister);
3810
3811 // If we reached the last element -> failure.
3812 failureCases.append(m_assembler.branch32(Assembler::Equal, Assembler::Address(spaceSplitStringData, SpaceSplitStringData::sizeMemoryOffset()), indexRegister));
3813 // Otherwise just loop over.
3814 m_assembler.jump().linkTo(loopStart, &m_assembler);
3815
3816 // Success case.
3817 classFound.link(&m_assembler);
3818 }
3819}
3820
3821void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateElementIsLink(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases)
3822{
3823 failureCases.append(m_assembler.branchTest32(Assembler::Zero, Assembler::Address(elementAddressRegister, Node::nodeFlagsMemoryOffset()), Assembler::TrustedImm32(Node::flagIsLink())));
3824}
3825
3826static bool nthFilterIsAlwaysSatisified(int a, int b)
3827{
3828 // Anything modulo 1 is zero. Unless b restricts the range, this does not filter anything out.
3829 if (a == 1 && (!b || (b == 1)))
3830 return true;
3831 return false;
3832}

3834void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateNthChildParentCheckAndRelationUpdate(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases, const SelectorFragment& fragment)
3835{
3836 LocalRegister parentNode(m_registerAllocator);
3837 generateWalkToParentNode(parentNode);
3838 failureCases.append(m_assembler.branchTestPtr(Assembler::Zero, parentNode));
3839 Assembler::Jump notElement = DOMJIT::branchTestIsElementFlagOnNode(m_assembler, Assembler::Zero, parentNode);
3840
3841 auto relation = fragmentMatchesRightmostOrAdjacentElement(fragment)
3842 ? Style::Relation::ChildrenAffectedByForwardPositionalRules
3843 : Style::Relation::DescendantsAffectedByForwardPositionalRules;
3844 generateAddStyleRelationIfResolvingStyle(parentNode, relation);
3845 Assembler::Jump parentNodeCheckEnd = m_assembler.jump();
3846
3847 notElement.link(&m_assembler);
3848 failureCases.append(DOMJIT::branchTestIsShadowRootFlagOnNode(m_assembler, Assembler::Zero, parentNode));
3849
3850 parentNodeCheckEnd.link(&m_assembler);
3851}

3853void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateElementIsNthChild(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases, const SelectorFragment& fragment)
3854{
3855 generateNthChildParentCheckAndRelationUpdate(failureCases, fragment);
3856
3857 Vector<std::pair<int, int>, 32> validSubsetFilters;
3858 validSubsetFilters.reserveInitialCapacity(fragment.nthChildFilters.size());
3859 for (const auto& slot : fragment.nthChildFilters) {
3860 if (nthFilterIsAlwaysSatisified(slot.first, slot.second))
3861 continue;
3862 validSubsetFilters.uncheckedAppend(slot);
3863 }
3864 if (validSubsetFilters.isEmpty())
3865 return;
3866
3867 // Setup the counter at 1.
3868 LocalRegisterWithPreference elementCounter(m_registerAllocator, JSC::GPRInfo::argumentGPR1);
3869 m_assembler.move(Assembler::TrustedImm32(1), elementCounter);
3870
3871 // Loop over the previous adjacent elements and increment the counter.
3872 {
3873 LocalRegister previousSibling(m_registerAllocator);
3874 m_assembler.move(elementAddressRegister, previousSibling);
3875
3876 // Getting the child index is very efficient when it works. When there is no child index,
3877 // querying at every iteration is very inefficient. We solve this by only testing the child
3878 // index on the first direct adjacent.
3879 Assembler::JumpList noMoreSiblingsCases;
3880
3881 Assembler::JumpList noCachedChildIndexCases;
3882 generateWalkToPreviousAdjacentElement(noMoreSiblingsCases, previousSibling);
3883
3884 LocalRegister elementRareData(m_registerAllocator);
3885 m_assembler.loadPtr(Assembler::Address(previousSibling, Node::rareDataMemoryOffset()), elementRareData);
3886
3887 LocalRegister rareDataPointerMask(m_registerAllocator);
3888 m_assembler.move(Assembler::TrustedImmPtr(Node::rareDataPointerMask()), rareDataPointerMask);
3889 m_assembler.andPtr(rareDataPointerMask, elementRareData);
3890
3891 noCachedChildIndexCases.append(m_assembler.branchTestPtr(Assembler::Zero, elementRareData));
3892 {
3893 LocalRegister cachedChildIndex(m_registerAllocator);
3894 m_assembler.load16(Assembler::Address(elementRareData, ElementRareData::childIndexMemoryOffset()), cachedChildIndex);
3895 noCachedChildIndexCases.append(m_assembler.branchTest32(Assembler::Zero, cachedChildIndex));
3896 m_assembler.add32(cachedChildIndex, elementCounter);
3897 noMoreSiblingsCases.append(m_assembler.jump());
3898 }
3899 noCachedChildIndexCases.link(&m_assembler);
3900 m_assembler.add32(Assembler::TrustedImm32(1), elementCounter);
3901
3902 Assembler::Label loopStart = m_assembler.label();
3903 generateWalkToPreviousAdjacentElement(noMoreSiblingsCases, previousSibling);
3904 m_assembler.add32(Assembler::TrustedImm32(1), elementCounter);
3905 m_assembler.jump().linkTo(loopStart, &m_assembler);
3906 noMoreSiblingsCases.link(&m_assembler);
3907 }
3908
3909 generateAddStyleRelationIfResolvingStyle(elementAddressRegister, Style::Relation::NthChildIndex, Assembler::RegisterID(elementCounter));
3910
3911 for (const auto& slot : validSubsetFilters)
3912 generateNthFilterTest(failureCases, elementCounter, slot.first, slot.second);
3913}
3914
3915void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateElementIsNthChildOf(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases, const SelectorFragment& fragment)
3916{
3917 generateNthChildParentCheckAndRelationUpdate(failureCases, fragment);
3918
3919 // The initial element must match the selector list.
3920 for (const NthChildOfSelectorInfo& nthChildOfSelectorInfo : fragment.nthChildOfFilters)
3921 generateElementMatchesSelectorList(failureCases, elementAddressRegister, nthChildOfSelectorInfo.selectorList);
3922
3923 Vector<const NthChildOfSelectorInfo*> validSubsetFilters;
3924 for (const NthChildOfSelectorInfo& nthChildOfSelectorInfo : fragment.nthChildOfFilters) {
3925 if (nthFilterIsAlwaysSatisified(nthChildOfSelectorInfo.a, nthChildOfSelectorInfo.b))
3926 continue;
3927 validSubsetFilters.append(&nthChildOfSelectorInfo);
3928 }
3929 if (validSubsetFilters.isEmpty())
3930 return;
3931
3932 for (const NthChildOfSelectorInfo* nthChildOfSelectorInfo : validSubsetFilters) {
3933 // Setup the counter at 1.
3934 LocalRegisterWithPreference elementCounter(m_registerAllocator, JSC::GPRInfo::argumentGPR1);
3935 m_assembler.move(Assembler::TrustedImm32(1), elementCounter);
3936
3937 // Loop over the previous adjacent elements and increment the counter.
3938 {
3939 LocalRegister previousSibling(m_registerAllocator);
3940 m_assembler.move(elementAddressRegister, previousSibling);
3941
3942 Assembler::JumpList noMoreSiblingsCases;
3943
3944 Assembler::Label loopStart = m_assembler.label();
3945
3946 generateWalkToPreviousAdjacentElement(noMoreSiblingsCases, previousSibling);
3947
3948 Assembler::JumpList localFailureCases;
3949 generateElementMatchesSelectorList(localFailureCases, previousSibling, nthChildOfSelectorInfo->selectorList);
3950 localFailureCases.linkTo(loopStart, &m_assembler);
3951 m_assembler.add32(Assembler::TrustedImm32(1), elementCounter);
3952 m_assembler.jump().linkTo(loopStart, &m_assembler);
3953
3954 noMoreSiblingsCases.link(&m_assembler);
3955 }
3956
3957 generateNthFilterTest(failureCases, elementCounter, nthChildOfSelectorInfo->a, nthChildOfSelectorInfo->b);
3958 }
3959}

3961void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateNthLastChildParentCheckAndRelationUpdate(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases, const SelectorFragment& fragment)
3962{
3963 LocalRegister parentNode(m_registerAllocator);
3964 generateWalkToParentNode(parentNode);
3965 failureCases.append(m_assembler.branchTestPtr(Assembler::Zero, parentNode));
3966 Assembler::Jump notElement = DOMJIT::branchTestIsElementFlagOnNode(m_assembler, Assembler::Zero, parentNode);
3967
3968 auto relation = fragmentMatchesRightmostOrAdjacentElement(fragment)
3969 ? Style::Relation::ChildrenAffectedByBackwardPositionalRules
3970 : Style::Relation::DescendantsAffectedByBackwardPositionalRules;
3971 generateAddStyleRelationIfResolvingStyle(parentNode, relation);
3972 failureCases.append(m_assembler.branchTest32(Assembler::Zero, Assembler::Address(parentNode, Node::nodeFlagsMemoryOffset()),
3973 Assembler::TrustedImm32(Node::flagIsParsingChildrenFinished())));
3974 Assembler::Jump parentNodeCheckEnd = m_assembler.jump();
3975
3976 notElement.link(&m_assembler);
3977 failureCases.append(DOMJIT::branchTestIsShadowRootFlagOnNode(m_assembler, Assembler::Zero, parentNode));
3978
3979 parentNodeCheckEnd.link(&m_assembler);
3980}
