3982void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateElementIsNthLastChild(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases, const SelectorFragment& fragment)
3983{
3984 generateNthLastChildParentCheckAndRelationUpdate(failureCases, fragment);
3985
3986 Vector<std::pair<int, int>, 32> validSubsetFilters;
3987 validSubsetFilters.reserveInitialCapacity(fragment.nthLastChildFilters.size());
3988 for (const auto& slot : fragment.nthLastChildFilters) {
3989 if (nthFilterIsAlwaysSatisified(slot.first, slot.second))
3990 continue;
3991 validSubsetFilters.uncheckedAppend(slot);
3992 }
3993 if (validSubsetFilters.isEmpty())
3994 return;
3995
3996 LocalRegister elementCounter(m_registerAllocator);
3997 { // Loop over the following sibling elements and increment the counter.
3998 LocalRegister nextSibling(m_registerAllocator);
3999 m_assembler.move(elementAddressRegister, nextSibling);
4000 // Setup the counter at 1.
4001 m_assembler.move(Assembler::TrustedImm32(1), elementCounter);
4002
4003 Assembler::JumpList noMoreSiblingsCases;
4004
4005 generateWalkToNextAdjacentElement(noMoreSiblingsCases, nextSibling);
4006
4007 Assembler::Label loopStart = m_assembler.label();
4008 m_assembler.add32(Assembler::TrustedImm32(1), elementCounter);
4009 generateWalkToNextAdjacentElement(noMoreSiblingsCases, nextSibling);
4010 m_assembler.jump().linkTo(loopStart, &m_assembler);
4011 noMoreSiblingsCases.link(&m_assembler);
4012 }
4013
4014 for (const auto& slot : validSubsetFilters)
4015 generateNthFilterTest(failureCases, elementCounter, slot.first, slot.second);
4016}

4020 generateNthLastChildParentCheckAndRelationUpdate(failureCases, fragment);

4040 m_assembler.move(Assembler::TrustedImm32(1), elementCounter);
4041
4042 // Loop over the following adjacent elements and increment the counter.
4043 {
4044 LocalRegister nextSibling(m_registerAllocator);
4045 m_assembler.move(elementAddressRegister, nextSibling);

4065
4066void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateElementMatchesNotPseudoClass(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases, const SelectorFragment& fragment)
4067{
4068 Assembler::JumpList localFailureCases;
4069 generateElementMatchesSelectorList(localFailureCases, elementAddressRegister, fragment.notFilters);
4070 // Since this is a not pseudo class filter, reaching here is a failure.
4071 failureCases.append(m_assembler.jump());
4072 localFailureCases.link(&m_assembler);
4073}
4074
4075void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateElementMatchesAnyPseudoClass(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases, const SelectorFragment& fragment)
4076{
4077 for (const auto& subFragments : fragment.anyFilters) {
4078 RELEASE_ASSERT(!subFragments.isEmpty());
4079
4080 // Don't handle the last fragment in this loop.
4081 Assembler::JumpList successCases;
4082 for (unsigned i = 0; i < subFragments.size() - 1; ++i) {
4083 Assembler::JumpList localFailureCases;
4084 generateElementMatching(localFailureCases, localFailureCases, subFragments[i]);
4085 successCases.append(m_assembler.jump());
4086 localFailureCases.link(&m_assembler);
4087 }
4088
4089 // At the last fragment, optimize the failure jump to jump to the non-local failure directly.
4090 generateElementMatching(failureCases, failureCases, subFragments.last());
4091 successCases.link(&m_assembler);
4092 }
4093}

4101void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateElementHasPseudoElement(Assembler::JumpList&, const SelectorFragment& fragment)
4102{
4103 ASSERT_UNUSED(fragment, fragment.pseudoElementSelector);
4104 ASSERT_WITH_MESSAGE(m_selectorContext != SelectorContext::QuerySelector, "When the fragment has pseudo element, the selector becomes CannotMatchAnything for QuerySelector and this test function is not called.");
4105 ASSERT_WITH_MESSAGE_UNUSED(fragment, fragmentMatchesTheRightmostElement(fragment), "Virtual pseudo elements handling is only effective in the rightmost fragment. If the current fragment is not rightmost fragment, CSS JIT compiler makes it CannotMatchAnything in fragment construction phase, so never reach here.");
4106}
4107
4108void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateRequestedPseudoElementEqualsToSelectorPseudoElement(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases, const SelectorFragment& fragment, Assembler::RegisterID checkingContext)
4109{
4110 ASSERT(m_selectorContext != SelectorContext::QuerySelector);
4111
4112 // Make sure that the requested pseudoId equals to the pseudo element of the rightmost fragment.
4113 // If the rightmost fragment doesn't have a pseudo element, the requested pseudoId need to be PseudoId::None to succeed the matching.
4114 // Otherwise, if the requested pseudoId is not PseudoId::None, the requested pseudoId need to equal to the pseudo element of the rightmost fragment.
4115 if (fragmentMatchesTheRightmostElement(fragment)) {
4116 if (!fragment.pseudoElementSelector)
4117 failureCases.append(m_assembler.branch8(Assembler::NotEqual, Assembler::Address(checkingContext, OBJECT_OFFSETOF(SelectorChecker::CheckingContext, pseudoId)), Assembler::TrustedImm32(static_cast<unsigned>(PseudoId::None))));
4118 else {
4119 Assembler::Jump skip = m_assembler.branch8(Assembler::Equal, Assembler::Address(checkingContext, OBJECT_OFFSETOF(SelectorChecker::CheckingContext, pseudoId)), Assembler::TrustedImm32(static_cast<unsigned>(PseudoId::None)));
4120 failureCases.append(m_assembler.branch8(Assembler::NotEqual, Assembler::Address(checkingContext, OBJECT_OFFSETOF(SelectorChecker::CheckingContext, pseudoId)), Assembler::TrustedImm32(static_cast<unsigned>(CSSSelector::pseudoId(fragment.pseudoElementSelector->pseudoElementType())))));
4121 skip.link(&m_assembler);
4122 }
4123 }
4124}

4133void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateElementIsScopeRoot(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases)
4134{
4135 ASSERT(m_selectorContext == SelectorContext::QuerySelector);
4136
4137 LocalRegister scope(m_registerAllocator);
4138 loadCheckingContext(scope);
4139 m_assembler.loadPtr(Assembler::Address(scope, OBJECT_OFFSETOF(SelectorChecker::CheckingContext, scope)), scope);
4140
4141 Assembler::Jump scopeIsNotNull = m_assembler.branchTestPtr(Assembler::NonZero, scope);
4142
4143 DOMJIT::loadDocument(m_assembler, elementAddressRegister, scope);
4144 DOMJIT::loadDocumentElement(m_assembler, scope, scope);
4145
4146 scopeIsNotNull.link(&m_assembler);
4147 failureCases.append(m_assembler.branchPtr(Assembler::NotEqual, scope, elementAddressRegister));
4148}

4156
4157void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateElementIsFirstLink(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases, Assembler::RegisterID element)
4158{
4159 LocalRegister currentElement(m_registerAllocator);
4160 m_assembler.loadPtr(m_stackAllocator.addressOf(m_startElement), currentElement);
4161
4162 // Tree walking up to the provided element until link node is found.
4163 Assembler::Label loopStart(m_assembler.label());
4164
4165 // The target element is always in the ancestors from the start element to the root node.
4166 // So the tree walking doesn't loop infinitely and it will be stopped with the following `currentElement == element` condition.
4167 Assembler::Jump reachedToElement = m_assembler.branchPtr(Assembler::Equal, currentElement, element);
4168
4169 failureCases.append(m_assembler.branchTest32(Assembler::NonZero, Assembler::Address(currentElement, Node::nodeFlagsMemoryOffset()), Assembler::TrustedImm32(Node::flagIsLink())));
4170
4171 // And these ancestors are guaranteed that they are element nodes.
4172 // So there's no need to check whether it is an element node and whether it is not a nullptr.
4173 m_assembler.loadPtr(Assembler::Address(currentElement, Node::parentNodeMemoryOffset()), currentElement);
4174 m_assembler.jump(loopStart);
4175
4176 reachedToElement.link(&m_assembler);
4177}

4181 m_assembler.storePtr(element, m_stackAllocator.addressOf(m_lastVisitedElement));
4182}
4183
4184void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateMarkPseudoStyleForPseudoElement(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases, const SelectorFragment& fragment)
4185{
4186 ASSERT(m_selectorContext != SelectorContext::QuerySelector);
4187
4188 // When fragment doesn't have a pseudo element, there's no need to mark the pseudo element style.
4189 if (!fragment.pseudoElementSelector)
4190 return;
4191
4192 LocalRegister checkingContext(m_registerAllocator);
4193 loadCheckingContext(checkingContext);
4194
4195 Assembler::JumpList successCases;
4196
4197 // When the requested pseudoId isn't PseudoId::None, there's no need to mark the pseudo element style.
4198 successCases.append(m_assembler.branch8(Assembler::NotEqual, Assembler::Address(checkingContext, OBJECT_OFFSETOF(SelectorChecker::CheckingContext, pseudoId)), Assembler::TrustedImm32(static_cast<unsigned>(PseudoId::None))));
4199
4200 // When resolving mode is CollectingRulesIgnoringVirtualPseudoElements, there's no need to mark the pseudo element style.
4201 successCases.append(branchOnResolvingModeWithCheckingContext(Assembler::Equal, SelectorChecker::Mode::CollectingRulesIgnoringVirtualPseudoElements, checkingContext));
4202
4203 // When resolving mode is ResolvingStyle, mark the pseudo style for pseudo element.
4204 PseudoId dynamicPseudo = CSSSelector::pseudoId(fragment.pseudoElementSelector->pseudoElementType());
4205 if (dynamicPseudo < PseudoId::FirstInternalPseudoId) {
4206 failureCases.append(branchOnResolvingModeWithCheckingContext(Assembler::NotEqual, SelectorChecker::Mode::ResolvingStyle, checkingContext));
4207
4208 Assembler::Address pseudoIDSetAddress(checkingContext, OBJECT_OFFSETOF(SelectorChecker::CheckingContext, pseudoIDSet));
4209 auto pseudoIDSetDataAddress = pseudoIDSetAddress.withOffset(PseudoIdSet::dataMemoryOffset());
4210 PseudoIdSet value { dynamicPseudo };
4211 m_assembler.store32(Assembler::TrustedImm32(value.data()), pseudoIDSetDataAddress);
4212 }
4213
4214 // We have a pseudoElementSelector, we are not in CollectingRulesIgnoringVirtualPseudoElements so
4215 // we must match that pseudo element. Since the context's pseudo selector is PseudoId::None, we fail matching
4216 // after the marking.
4217 failureCases.append(m_assembler.jump());
4218
4219 successCases.link(&m_assembler);
4220}
4221
4222void SelectorCodeGenerator::generateNthFilterTest(Assembler::JumpList& failureCases, Assembler::RegisterID counter, int a, int b)
4223{
4224 if (!a)
4225 failureCases.append(m_assembler.branch32(Assembler::NotEqual, Assembler::TrustedImm32(b), counter));
4226 else if (a > 0) {
4227 if (a == 2 && b == 1) {
4228 // This is the common case 2n+1 (or "odd"), we can test for odd values without doing the arithmetic.
4229 failureCases.append(m_assembler.branchTest32(Assembler::Zero, counter, Assembler::TrustedImm32(1)));
4230 } else {
4231 if (b) {
4232 LocalRegister counterCopy(m_registerAllocator);
4233 m_assembler.move(counter, counterCopy);
4234 failureCases.append(m_assembler.branchSub32(Assembler::Signed, Assembler::TrustedImm32(b), counterCopy));
4235 moduloIsZero(failureCases, counterCopy, a);
4236 } else
4237 moduloIsZero(failureCases, counter, a);
4238 }
4239 } else {
4240 LocalRegister bRegister(m_registerAllocator);
4241 m_assembler.move(Assembler::TrustedImm32(b), bRegister);
4242
4243 failureCases.append(m_assembler.branchSub32(Assembler::Signed, counter, bRegister));
4244 moduloIsZero(failureCases, bRegister, a);
4245 }
4246}
